I have been visiting this gym often and like the environment but recently, I was approached by a personal trainer out of nowhere once I started resting during a workout. He was telling me about the evolt machine and benefits and kept being pushy. He kept asking me about my schedule and when I would come to the gym. He also assumed “you come when you feel like it?” before I could tell him when I would usually come to the gym. After a while, I was clearly not interested and told him that I’ll try it out the following week. I also said I’m busy most days and I was trying to finish my workout quickly at the time but he kept asking me the specific days and timings I would show up to the gym. Throughout the conversation, he was being pushy, somewhat intimidating and very pressuring. It isn’t easy to workout alone as a woman and this interaction left a bad taste.

If I wanted to try out the evolt machine or wanted personal training, I would’ve approached the staff myself. Did not feel comfortable after this interaction and I don’t think I’ll show up often anymore.

A Gift of Love Across the Miles – My Experience with Computers for Moms

Today, I finally received both gaming laptops for my daughters in the Philippines, and soon, they’ll be in their hands. Being far away is never easy, but knowing they’ll have something special from me makes the distance feel smaller. These laptops aren’t just devices—they’re a symbol of my love and support. Thank you, Computers for Moms, for helping me bring joy to my girls.

I've been buying refurbished laptops from Computers for Moms for a while now, and they never disappoint.

The quality is consistently excellent - clean, reliable machines that perform like new.

Prices are fair, shipping is usually fast, and everything is well-packaged.

With Computers for Moms, refurbished doesn’t mean second-rate — it means reliable, affordable, and high quality. Highly recommend if you want a dependable laptop without the premium price tag

Review Text: I tried to call the outlet to ask regarding my C&C parcel to which 8 of it went to voicemail. So I decided to just head down to the store to ask personally. Business Name: UNIQLO Causeway Point (Same Day Click & Collect)
Review Text:
It has been a disappointing shopping experience for me today; A "Limited Offer" sign caused confusion. It was in the middle of two types of pants and it lead me to think that this offer spreads is for both of the pants. The sign was not specific that the offer would only be for a certain pant. So I chose a pant, spent time in the fitting room and queuing too, only for them to tell me that there was no discount. I had to go back to the place as I thought I had read wrongly but I realised that I would not be the only one who would be confused, as their placement of pants and that Limited Offer sign can cause confusion. After our feedback to the various staffs,  they tried to reach out to the manager who in the end, did not bother coming out and attending to us which I found irresponsible.
We are aware that regardless, there will be no compensation. However, we do hope that they make the shopping experience easier; shifting the pants accordingly.

He really help to diagnosed my pc as it wasn’t turning on. He even spots that something is wrong with my ram and helped to replace it. He fixed my pc less than an hour! Will come back soon if there’s anything wrong with my pc.

Charles was very in the know of PC building and repair as the issue was identified briefly and he offered solutions clearly and concisely without upselling at all. Overall really a hidden gem of a service located up north of Singapore. I had never written a Google review before even after being prompted by many establishments, but the experience and service is top notch to not recommend!

I found Shining PC on Carousell. I had a CPU & GPU pair in mind (7800X3D + 4070Ti Super) and was open to recommendations for the rest of the build. I asked Charles for his recommendations based on what I would use the PC for, and he was very friendly and knowledgeable. He did not try to upsell me any components and even told me 4070TS is too much for my use case lol! He also answered my other questions patiently. Even though I texted him late at night, his replies were quick.

I paid a deposit a few hours later on Sunday morning (6 AM) and the PC was delivered the very next day on Monday. He gave me timely updates on the assembly, testing and delivery. He also helped to hook up the PC to my monitors and accessories to check if everything was good and if I had any questions.

I previously got a PC from the famous “A” brand and I must say the service is day and night. On top of that, the price given by Charles is very competitive (actually, it is even more affordable than the other few merchants I asked). I definitely recommend anyone looking for a custom PC to look for Shining PC. Enjoying my new PC as I type this review, thank you so much Charles. :)
Amazing guy help me with everything can’t wait to build. Thank you

Came across this shop on carousell while looking for options and saw there was a lot of reviews. Did some more snooping around to make sure was credible as I had some doubts with such fantastic reviews but I am glad it was unfounded.

I have some background knowledge having built my own pc before but due to time constraints and life, decided to seek services to assemble all. So I was looking into the parts that boss recommended and I could see that he knows his stuff well. The guy was patient and quick in his response to answer my queries.

Finally, the time from confirming build to assembly to delivery was really fast, am grateful for delivering all the boxes as well promptly. Wasn't expecting him to offer to setup too and I knew how to so I thought it was fine. I didn't think he'd also have a video prepared in case so big ups for that! All in all, pretty satisfied from this purchase and I recommend!

Outstanding service offered by an honest and patient proprietor - Charles. I've built and upgraded my own PCs in the last couple of decades and now with too much on my plate, decided to seek help after seeing their incredibly high feedback score on Carousell.
Since I'm already quite familiar with what needs to be done, Charles was very patient with my questions and demands, in upgrading my PC to exactly what I wanted. And this includes cloning my OS onto the new system (which is famously troublesome thanks to a certain OS software). He also offered good suggestions against my initial requirements which I verified and accepted.
Specific parts were obtained for my upgrade and to top it off, he fixed up my PC by the next day! My PC is rocking well in exactly the way I want it and I earnestly recommend their services to anyone who needs help with their PCs.

The item is reasonable price.  It’s very cheap compare to the shop/seller.  And Charles is helpful,  friendly and he is knowledgeable.  He is very patient to explain all my query about my pc not only about the repair.   Legit & trusted seller.  Highly recommended

Charles was exceptionally helpful in diagnosing my pc that frequently BSOD, and lately when powered up no screen. He ran through couple of stress test and determined the problem is not my PC but probably one of my peripherals that is causing the issue. True enough. By process of elimination the problem was really my power strip which Charles did suggested for me to check.

And for all the trouble, he did not charge me any fee even when I insist on paying for his time.

Highly recommended for his expertise and honesty if anyone has hardware issues or need a new built for gaming or workstation.
Very nice owner who replies very fast and help me fixed my CPU power supply

I was researching on a new custom rig for fps games (valorant etc etc) as my old pre built was causing a lot of problems for me. I had very little knowledge about custom builds, but Charles was very patient and responsive to all my queries and I learnt a lot through the conversations we had, we even had a discussion that lasted a month regarding the specs of my custom build . Finally after many messages on carousell and whatsapp i settled for this beautiful beast.

What I really like from Charles is that he is honest and transparent about what parts is necessary for the purpose of the PC and will not over offer things that you do not need, he is also patient and provides quick and easy to understand answers to all your questions. He also tailors to your needs for example, I was not very into the March Promo case that was used as default so he offered me many more options for my budget, these little steps shows how professional and niche he at his job.

Highly recommended to anyone looking to build a custom PC that will last for ages.

Great store, Charles was patient and friendly, explained the whole issue with my PC and recommended appropriate parts to replace. The price was fair and service was fast. So hard to find store that do diagnostic and repair on the spot these days. Greatly recommended.

Review Text:
Had lunch at Food Republic in 313 Mall. Saw a new stall “Yuen Kee Dumplings” so we decided to give it a try.

There was a queue of 7 waiting to place their orders, while another maybe 5 other patrons waiting at the side for their meals to be prepared.

Got to place our orders after about 10 minutes, thereafter waited another 10 minutes for our orders to be ready.

We ordered their “popular” Shrimp & Crab Roe Wanton in Cantonese Style Soup. We were allowed to choose the type of soup or finishes (spicy, garlic, etc). $10.80.

Also the Chives & Pork Dumplings (like gyoza). For this we chose Viral Mixed Sauce with Chilli. $7.80.

The 10 Wantons were pretty big, wrapped with lots of shrimps and some crab roe, however I tasted like Ikura. The soup was clear and tasty. Overall quite good.

There were 9 pieces of Chives & Pork Dumplings in the other order. The sauce was something like chilli garlic sauce but not so heavy. They were sprinkled with peanut sauces. We found the flour wraps a little “rough”; but tasted nice overall.

Prices were reasonable.

We finished our meal with our favorite Yuan Yang from the Toast Box Stall, next door.

I'm usually quite hesitant to leave negative reviews but I hope this won't be the experience of others in the future. I was at Paragon today and really needed to charge my phone and when I walked past the concierge I noticed that they had a sign stating that they offer portable chargers. When I went up to ask if I could borrow or rent one, the lady at the concierge didn't even look at me until i paused to wait for her to look up and assumed she was busy even though she already said "hi" while looking down. She then told me I had to pay a $50 deposit to borrow the portable charger, which I am completely fine with and understand the need for. She appeared shocked when I said I was fine with the $50 deposit so I just said it again that I was completely fine with it. She continued staring at me and just said "$50 deposit" which honestly confused me because she didn't ask me how I wanted to pay and didn't tell me only cash was accepted and repeated it until I asked her if only cash payment was available. I then told her that i didn't have cash and asked if card payment was available to which she replied "there's an ATM"... I don't carry cash around and that's not her fault but I really think that for a mall like  paragon that the staff, especially at the concierge to have some sort of customer service training. I also think it would be a good idea to allow for card payment for the $50 deposit as many don't carry cash anymore especially if it is advertised at the concierge.

Paragon exudes sophistication from the moment you step in. Its interior design features airy dual atria, sleek wide corridors across six levels, and natural light flooding through clerestory windows all wrapped in warm timber tones and veined stone finishes. The space feels refined yet inviting, balancing luxury with a welcoming atmosphere.

This is a premier destination for upscale fashion and designer labels. Inside, you’ll find an enviable collection of international luxury brands like Gucci (home to a five-storey flagship), Prada, Givenchy, Burberry as well as accessible luxury names such as Coach and Miu Miu. The mix caters to a wide range of shoppers, offering depth without sacrificing prestige.

Paragon also shines when it comes to food, offering everything from casual cafés to fine dining. Highlights include Michelin-starred Crystal Jade Golden Palace and the luxurious Imperial Treasure Super Peking Duck restaurant.

If you’re looking for a luxe yet approachable shopping experience in Singapore, Paragon delivers on multiple fronts: beautiful architecture, top-tier brand selection, diverse dining, and great accessibility. Whether you’re browsing high fashion or stopping for a gourmet meal, it’s a stylish and elevated destination that impresses.

I even requested and do not mind to take the very last slot but still that nurse refused me and ask me to find other clinics which I was not able to find as they were all closed. 我是新加坡人也第一次来这间诊所的 登记时多问了一些问题柜台小姐显得很不耐烦态度极度恶劣 量血压是站着的 测量时 由于我是伤风感冒因此刻意把脸和身体斜向她 她却以很不友善的口气让我站好来 而且还把我的年龄给输入多10岁进电脑里 医生态度就相当不错 但收费颇高 看诊费就$60加上药整整就收费$90.50。

Dr Adrian is amazing! Truly empathetic, meticulous, humorous and assuring. A doctor who warrants a re-visit without hesitation.

However, there is huge room for improvement at the counter. We were on time for appointment,  waited 10 minutes and was attended to Dr Adrian promptly. Next, was a 20-minute wait for medicine and the clinic was empty. I am an advocate of respect towards service staff and I believe this should be mutual when handling patients. We checked in every 10-minute intervals because my elderly mother is feeling unwell. For the first check, Nurse Stella who was busy, told me to take a seat and that her colleagues would attend to me when it is ready. We didn’t hear anything after 10 minutes. Before we knew it, there was a patient who walked in to purchase medicine off the shelf and he was attended to promptly by another nurse. After he collected his medicine and made his payment, we were still waiting to be called. When we checked on status again, nurse Stella got visibly irritated, spoke louder and told us that the medicine had to be reviewed by the doctor. Then, she nudged her colleague to speed up and commented loudly “faster, patient asked and asked”. It was as if it was deliberate. When her colleague finally ended the call, I realised the main holdup was because the name labels had yet to be pasted on the prescribed medicine. It reflects absolute inefficiency and also disrespect for patients’ time. I would have understood if they were busy and explained why they needed more time. But, what I could not appreciate, was the lacklustre attitude demonstrated at the counter.

They asked me to come the next morning. I said I could not make a promise. It’s their mistake. Not mine. After two calls they finally apologized oh God.

This is probably one of the most westerly restaurants (the other being the one at Raffles Marina near the second link) in Singapore. Located in Tuas West, this restaurant is located in a 'ulu' industrial flat, amongst factories and industrial buildings.
The Place:
The hugh dining hall was decorated with many posters of food and LED wordings on the walls, which, together with the plastic plants, seem somewhat crowded and tacky. The bar counter was too crowded with equipments and utensils, and was overshadowed by the large posters hanging over it. The decor could improve with a better interior designer.
The Food
I had the truffles olio aglio pasta with New Zealand ribeye. The pasta was perfectly cooked, with a nice degree of al-dente. The truffles oil add a hint of umami to the olive oil-based sauce, without overpowering it. The ribeye was a bit tough, probably due to the lack of marbling of the New Zealand steak, but was well cooked and not dry, attesting to the skill and care of the chef. The addition of black cavier on the steak, although did not add to the flavour, however did enhance the presentation of the dish. The restaurant was having a promotion of Japanese oysters - $1 for each raw oyster. The plump oyster tasted full of briny freshness, and was creamy in textual.
Conclusion
It is worth a visit if you are around the area.

Greenhouse Bistro is a charming and cozy dining destination tucked away at 30 Tuas Bay Drive, offering a refreshing escape from the industrial surroundings of Tuas. It is well-known for its relaxed atmosphere, spacious setting, and greenery-inspired decor, making it a welcoming place for both casual diners and those looking to host small gatherings like company lunches, team celebrations, or birthday parties.

The bistro prides itself on serving a diverse menu, combining both Western and Asian cuisines, ensuring that there’s something for everyone. Diners can expect a good selection of dishes, including pasta, grilled meats, local favorites, and fusion creations. The food is well-prepared and served in generous portions, making it a satisfying meal experience.

One of the standout features of Greenhouse Bistro is its comfortable and airy ambiance. The seating is well-spaced, and the greenery-themed decor gives the space a relaxing, garden-like vibe, which is quite rare in the Tuas area. It’s a perfect spot to unwind after a long day at work or simply enjoy a leisurely lunch with friends or colleagues.

In addition to dine-in services, Greenhouse Bistro also offers islandwide delivery and self-pickup options, making it convenient for those who prefer to enjoy their meals from home or the office. Customers have praised their efficient service and the consistent quality of their food, whether dining in or ordering for delivery.

Overall, Greenhouse Bistro is a hidden gem in Tuas. It offers not only delicious food but also a peaceful and inviting setting, making it an ideal choice for anyone in the area looking for a comfortable place to enjoy a good meal. Whether you’re visiting for a quick lunch, a group gathering, or ordering in, Greenhouse Bistro delivers a satisfying dining experience.

Homeground Gym Jurong West is exactly what this neighborhood needed! As soon as you walk in, you feel the welcoming community vibe – it’s not just a gym, it’s a place where everyone genuinely wants to help you reach your goals. The equipment is top-notch, and they have everything from strength machines to cardio gear, all brand new and well-maintained. I love that it’s science-based and data-driven, so I know my workouts are backed by research. The personal trainers here are awesome – super knowledgeable and really focus on sustainable progress rather than quick fixes. Plus, the live occupancy feature is a game-changer, letting me plan my workouts around busy times. Can’t recommend it enough for anyone looking for a serious, results-oriented gym experience in Jurong West!

The gym is equipped with state-of-the-art machines, and the variety of fitness classes they offer is fantastic—there’s something for everyone! However, the Uniqlo staff did not allow this change. This kind of inflexibility made me very frustrated, and in the end, I received nothing from this promotion.

I ordered a pair of jeans and a shirt online for a company dinner and the app suggested size 40 for the jeans. Unfortunately, that size was too big and I went down to Jurong Point store to make an exchange the following day.

Truthfully, I was dissatisfied with the way the Supervisor there handled this issue.  He did not seem keen to provide the necessary assistance.

He checked for a while but informed me that the system wasn't updated and that there wasn't much he could do. Is it my problem that the system was not updated?

I do realize that he could have approached or made a call to other management for assistance but he failed. I asked if there was any other way for me to make an exchange and he informed me he could help to check with the other stores except that I have to travel to that particular store for the exchange but he didn't make the call. I could not believe it as I knew that some outlets would provide inter-store transfers upon request.

He also suggested exchanging for other items which I was not keen on.

Since he could not provide a further solution to this issue, I left the store but returned to him shortly as I wasn't satisfied with his “don't care” attitude. I showed him that the online has available pieces but he kept telling me his system was not updated.

Eventually, to avoid further dissatisfaction, I left the store feeling annoyed and furious. I know he could do something but he chose not to.

Finally, I managed to obtain the exchange from other outlets. A bad experience from this outlet.

The cleanliness of the gym’s toilets could definitely use some attention. Additionally, the management needs to focus on enforcing gym rules consistently to ensure fairness among all users. For instance, despite the gym’s policy requiring proper attire, I’ve noticed several instances where members were either barefoot or wearing slippers, which raises safety concerns.

To add to that, just yesterday, I saw someone using the treadmill shirtless. This not only poses a hygiene issue—with sweat potentially spreading onto the equipment—but also creates an uncomfortable environment. What’s more concerning is that this happened while a staff member was present, yet no action was taken. It leaves me wondering what the staff is actually doing during their shifts and how they’re ensuring a safe and hygienic experience for everyone. There’s definitely room for improvement in these areas.

It's really, really annoying.

Otherwise the gym is not bad tho.
Friendly environment
The check in and sign in process was so smooth and very fast thanks to William who helped me and answered all my questions! Thank you!
Worst
Its ok for foreign workers
Newly renovated with good equipment. 4 power racks and 1 deadlift platform with a variety of machines
Place is spacious and clean. In terms of customer service, super happy with Khalis. He will answer all your problematic questions professionally and with patience. Well done dude!

Spacious gym. Could do with more 5, 10 and 12.5kg dumbbells and sanitising sprays & cloths to wipe equipments and benches after using. I noticed hardly any members wipe down after using. Also noticed most lockers were locked while the gym was not full and members at that time kept their bags at the alternative wooden shelves during my visit (Sep 24, around 2pm).
But never visited
Place is Not conducive and most of the gym goers and polite.

Dr. Ferguson provides thorough explanations, ensuring that patients fully understand their treatment options. His procedures are precise and efficient, demonstrating a high level of expertise. Additionally, he takes his responsibilities seriously, showing a strong sense of professionalism and dedication to patient care.

Ms. Nurul, dental assistant, is also very attentive and professional, working seamlessly with Dr. Ferguson to ensure smooth and efficient treatments. Furthermore, the clinic manages appointments well, accommodating scheduling requests and ensuring a smooth booking process.

Thanks to both of them, I can enjoy my meals comfortably without any pain or concerns about my teeth. I truly hope they will continue to take care of my dental health in the future.
A great clinic. Can't complain.
Dr ferguson helped me w wisdom tooth extraction and he was really really nice and patient :) the receptionists are also really sweet, surgery was smooth and quick

Highly recommend Dr. Ferguson for his professionalism. He takes the time to explain dental procedures and concepts with great clarity and, when necessary, shows research papers. Thanks to him, I have maintained good oral health through years of visits.

Dr. Elizabeth at FC Dental is very professional and patient. After a quick examination, she pinpointed the problem with my teeth and proposed a scientific step-by-step treatment plan. I feel very lucky to have met a doctor like her.
I just don’t understand why the internal staffs never align info together. I need to go back and forth to ask and the staffs’ attitude were all terrible. The process was totally a mess too.

Dr. Mok who works every Wednesday is really irresponsible.

40 days ago I paid a very high price to have a tooth fixed. After about 40 days, the filling developed a problem and it hurt when I drank cold water. So, I suspect that the material has fallen out, but of course, it could be something else, so I want to go for a review. Dr. Mok said she would remove the previous material and replace it with one that was temporary and did not guarantee results. I expressed my concern because once the medication failed, my teeth would be exposed and more damage would be done. Then,  after I refused to use this material, I asked if I could use the original material and Dr. Mok refused. So I decided not to change because, after all, no one wants to revert to a temporary, less good-looking material without taking that much risk. Dr. Mok went on to say that if I were to leave, she would have to take a photograph of my teeth to prove that there was nothing wrong with her fillings. I thought this was utterly ridiculous. If she was so adamant that there was no problem, why did she change me to a bad material in the first place? If I don't change the material, do I have to prove that her padding is fine? I felt that she was simply shirking her responsibility. She would not allow me to leave if I refused to have my photo taken because the case had to be documented. High charges + bad attitude + shirking responsibility make me very unhappy and I hope someone will pay attention to this matter.
Over charging and waiting for long hour

Today I went back to Dr Mok for tooth cleaning. As usual, Dr Mok is professional and gentle. I knew her in Nov, 2020, when I went to have the wisdom tooth removed. There was an extreme pain due to the pressure induced from the wisdom tooth. I expressed my suffer to the young lady in the counter, after a short check, she decided to let me in during the Dr’s break time. After x-ray, Dr Mok discussed the condition of the two visible wisdom teeth with me. Then everything went through smoothly. Blood stopped hours later. Quick recovery (2~3 days) and no pain after removing one wisdom tooth. One week later, I went for a bite wing x-ray to check risk of cavities (one-time check valid for 3 years) and had normal tooth cleaning.
The service is excellent, though the price is a little high (even with student discount). But Dr Mok and her assistant can be trusted!

Today at 4 pm I went for consulting a pain headache resulting from tooth decay after got 2 X-ray was done. Don't know why the dentist recommended scaling and cleaning but never do the filing of my decay tooth. At night I can't sleep because of toothache. He should know which to piority first. I paid $219 for the service. Next morning I had to go another dentist. Very frustrated.

Terrible service!
They need two months to make a crown that typically takes two weeks!
Impressioned for the first time and was told a few days later that need to take another impression. No reason explained.
They keep rescheduling my appointment for a single treatment. Was rescheduled many times just for a crown treatment, including a last-minute change.

The orthodontics treatment by Dr. Mok is truly a nice experience for me. She is very professional in designing the treatment plan. Every time doing the adjustment, she not only checks the teeth condition carefully,  but also listens patiently to my feelings and request for teeth and adjusts the treatment accordingly. She always thinks for the patients, and recommend the most suitable, and economic choice for me. I actually spent a quite reasonable price for the entire treatment. The results turn out to be good. I am satisficed with the teeth now and have cultivate good teeth caring habits. Thanks so much to Dr. Mok.
Dr Ng is very experienced, nice and kind. I'm grateful to have her diagnosis and treatment.

Many thinks to Dr NG and Sher Pei. I suffered from serious toothache recently due to the wisdom tooth. It caused a terrible swollen face and pain of my left face. I even could not sleep these days and felt extremely painful. It is Sher Pei, helpful and nice, who helped me make appointments and recommended me to Dr NG. For Dr NG, she is very experienced,kind and warm and she gave me lots of encouragement! With her professional help, I feel much more better right now.I am so lucky and grateful to meet them in Fullerton Dental in NTU.

Went for my wisdom teeth extractions and I must say it had been a really pleasant experience. My extractions involved both extractions and surgeries which my dentist, Dr Ng did it smoothly. She assured me many times during the process which calmed a first timer like me alot. And I must say overall she did it so well and stitched the wounds such that i did not experience much pain post-extractions which I'm really grateful for. An amazing experience, would recommend NTU students/staffs to go to

I am a patient at this dental clinic from the last 5 years or so. If I have last this long it is because I have been always assisted by Dr. Mock. She is highly professional. She always take great care of explaining things very carefully. This is very useful for one to understand what is the situation one is facing. Knowing well the situation helps you a lot a when taking an important decision. She works with great dedication and has a strong commitment to quality. Because of all these reasons and my confidence on her, I decided to face a few serious and complicated treatments, like surgical implants, happily, all successful. I am very satisfied with Dr. Mock and I believe I will continue working with her. The negative side is that perhaps the costs at the clinic are high. It would be great if Fullerton Dental would revisit their prices. It is true that the clinical instrumentation is quite advance, but still...

Dr Ferguson at Fullerton Dental @ NTU is the kindest and most thorough dentist that I have ever encountered. He is always concerned of my wellbeing during the treatments. I could really relax during my root cannel treatment. Seriously he is the best. The receptionist Sher Pie is also very professional and kind.

I went to Fullerton Dental clinic at NTU more than 1 year ago and I always felt very good treated, specially by Dr Mok and Dr Ng.
Maybe they charge a bit more than other clinics, but in may case I prefer a very good job than a cheap one: I already experienced that cheap becomes expensive at the very end, I lost 3 tooth due to cheap treatments
In addition, I have to say Dr Mok is really gentle on treat and during her practice, always being professional and honest with all the solutions she proposed regarding my medical treatment

Visited the clinic for the first time due to bleeding gums and suspected tooth decay. Dr Mok attended to me and did a thorough check, including x-ray. She explained to me the condition of my teeth, with the x-ray images and the sort of treatment required and the number of times required. It was detailed enough and I knew the breakdown of cost after my initial visit. Everything went well and my gums are in much better condition now. Thank you, Dr Mok. See you soon.

I had just completed my orthodontics under Dr. Mok. She was always careful and patient. The experience was great.

Before the orthodontics, I was suggested to have deep teeth scaling. My gum was seriously swollen and teeth were shaky. The doctor said that it would be harmful to wear the braces with serious gum problems. I thought the advice was reasonable so I took the treatments. Can't deny that the price was a bit high, but it worth considering the service and results. My gums became healthier and were ready for the latter process.

It is always a pleasant experience to receive treatment from Dr Mok. She provides absolutely painless treatment. Her professional manner is excellent and she always rises to the combined challenge of providing expert application of both technical and social skills. I have been a regular patient during the past 3 - 4 years, with some tricky surgery to experience. There has never been a call to question the decision making. Dr Mok is considerate and articulate in her approach to providing an excellent service. Highly recommended.

I would not recommend anyone to go to this clinic. Had mild gums problems and the doctor (Dr. Mok) exaggerated them and asked me to do four sessions to finish up teeth scaling. I paid 400 dollars for the first visit and decided to cancel the rest of the appointments. It is a rip-off and I wonder why a dental clinic on the campus would only care about profit rather than the well-being of patients. I then went to another clinic and had completely different experience. The doctor told me that my gums problems are not serious at all and only advised to go back for another check in one month. Most important, I was only charged 150 dollars for the treatment! So if you must go to the campus clinic, avoid Dr Mok (she is on duty on Wednesdays). I hope she is the only one like this in the clinic. Otherwise, shame on the clinic!

A follow-up: So I gave them the benefit of doubt after they told me that they saw my review and listened to the doctor's explanations, albeit belated, for the fees and her rationale for the arrangement of the treatment. She claims that she did not my email that I sent her earlier enquiring why so many sessions were needed. Although it seems really odd that the email (which I sent through my NTU work email address) did not go to her gmail, let's just believe it is a technical problem. She also explains to me why she did not refer me to a specialist during the first visit because she thought she could handle it. All in all, she tried to explain everything to me, and yet I am not quite fully convinced to be honest. I just wish that the communication could have been done earlier and more effectively. I also hope that doctors could be more cautious and thoughtful when providing their medical advice in the future. And I encourage those who are going to seek dental service to speak for their needs and communicate immediately whenever you have doubts.
On another note, I appreciate their good attitude and desire to communicate with me.
Dental cleaning service was ok but the counter service was meh.
Good and quick service from Chai Yuh at Fullerton Ntu. She was very nice and friendly and allowed me to complete my checkup fast despite crowd.

Dr Tsao and his assistant are very patient throughout. They keep assuring me not to worry. For people who are afraid of visiting dentist like me, I would like to recommend looking for Dr Tsao. Thank you.

Great service by Sher Pei. She is patient and helpful. Dr David Loh is very professional, alleviate my anxiety and worries by explaining the procedures thoroughly and patiently. Highly recommended. Thanks Both!
Dr David Loh and Sher Pei are great.
Experienced deep scaling under Dr Tsao. Not only was he gentle but he was precise. I never felt uncomfortable during the process. The best dental service I experienced.

Downtown East Branch

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text:
Comfort food! Go for the signature beef noodles with the thickest noodle choice. It's delicious. I have tried all the different types of noodles. The thicker ones are very qq and brings the dish to another level!

The broth is abit salty but that makes it even more delicious. Limited seating available but the service is very fast. Must try!

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text: A variety of noodle types to choose from and they are all long cut.. soup taste is mild but not bland. Pig stomach comes in big pieces, tendons are small pieces.. Table kinda squeeze, still ok for a quick meal.

Review Text: Came in a weekday for dinner. Not too crowded. The mala tendon noodles is tasty, although I felt the ingredients were too little compared to other outlets I have been to. Overall still tasty.

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text:
Lanzhou beef noodle at downtown east is our family go-to comfort food! It’s well liked by the kids for their delicious and filling beef noodles! All of us love the thick noodle thickness and slurping away!

The place is also extremely kids friendly, they have lots of child seat, kids utensils and also scissors are provided.

The place is also halal certified, suitable for our Muslim friends.

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text:
The food here has seen improvement and only got tastier, compared to the time this outlet first started. This has shown that the restaurant took pride in delivering quality products and service, by going great lengths to read and listen to feedbacks from customers.

However what made the dining experience exceptional was the exceptional service Zaim rendered. He’s 100% an invaluable staff - never fails to put on a smile whenever interacting customers, greets incoming and outgoing customers, thanking them for their support when leaving, very respectful, attentive to diners needs and remained courteous throughout

During the lull period - he will be seen keeping the counter and tables clean and tidy, while doing so he would periodically turn to check if any customers would require his attention, check on the equipments functionality etc.

All I could say is that Zaim does not realise his true potential in what he could deliver and I sincerely hope his employer or his future employer could help him see it. Well done!!

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text: The dry beef noodles is very nice. Teh noodles is ‘la mian’. The soup that accompanied it is very tasty but tasted like a lot of msg.

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text: Generous portions of noodles in tasty broth. The tripe goes very well with vinegar. Delicious!
We ordered the Royal Platter, deserts and drinks. All were delicious.
This is a halal Thai restaurant, the steam fish is good. Service from staff as per standard restaurant.
This is a halal thai restaurant located at a very nice and cooling hdb atea. Staff are nice and polite.

I love eating at this place. This has been my go to restaurant for the past year. This is because or the welcoming and kind staff! There also is a variety of food choices and the food is of high quality and the portion is also very decent. One of the staff that I really like even my family likes her is San San she is very friendly towards all customers and always is willing to go the extra mile!

best place to eat halal thai food!! i have been frequenting here for over a year & the food is seriously yummy. the tomyum here is good and the fish is always fresh. happy that the prices are decent as well.

hopefully the standards never drop! if they continue to stay consistent, i will forever be a loyal customer >< come down and support~

Nice experience. My family always frequent this restaurant. One of the staff is extremely kind and helpful always helping us. The staff also do their job well. The food was good as usual. There is a large variety of Thai meals in the menu. It is also children friendly because of the kids menu that they provide. Overall awesome experience!

Service and ambiance are good.
Food is average.

My family and I have dined at this Thai restaurant three times over the span of two years. Our first experience was genuinely enjoyable — the dishes were flavorful and left us wanting to return.

However, on our second and third visits, the quality noticeably declined. We ordered similar items each time: the spicy lemongrass lime fish, tofu with spinach, and Tom Yum (chicken or seafood). Unfortunately, after both recent visits, all of us developed severe sore throats, which may suggest a heavy use of MSG.

Beyond that, the flavors didn’t feel as authentic as we had hoped. The balance of spices and ingredients seemed off, and the overall experience left us disappointed.

While we appreciated our initial meal here, the inconsistency and potential health concerns have made us reluctant to return. Sadly, I don’t think we’ll be coming back.
yummy yummy in my tummy. love the service and can use cdc!
Food was superb with authentic Thai taste. Service was even better, kids got bouncy castle and token to play gumball machine. Vishal was kind and fast service too. Will come back!

Good halal Thai food. The seabass was fresh and while the pad thai was alright, the accompanying ribeye is really delicious. Would come back for the ribeye.

Restaurant ambience and decorations is Thai oriented and well furnished.

Passed by and takeaway the green curry with beef. Reached home opened the package and saw this whole chunk of beef lump together. Not good. The curry is very spicy and watery I wondered what is this. Thai green curry wasn’t supposed to be like this.
First time trying this and this would be the last.

Very2 sedap. I took the ribeye fried rice which is 14.80 and it was worth it.  A lot of food choice which most of which are Thai and fusion. If don’t want individual meal or with family u can buy sets such as a huge sea bass  set, Tom yam and much more. Quite tasty and delicious for its rather fair price. Ate here multiple times bc very sedap. Also, the service is good. U just need to scan a QR code then can order if u have trouble the waiters can help. The waiters and chefs also cook quite fast like abt 10-20 mins and the food reaches fast. The atmosphere here is really relaxing bc not much ppl go here and peak hours it’s not as much as other restaurants prob bc it’s in the heartlands. Would recommend u to try!
Food serving is fast, food is tasty, the service attendant done a great job in facilitating the crowd flow. Will come back again to try other dishes.
Nice environment with choices of food. Affordable and good services.

Have been here a few times. Staff are friendly and helpful. Food is okay - nothing particular to rave about. The mango sticky rice is a bit of a hit or miss - sometimes the mango is sour , sometimes it is sweet. Was quite disappointed to find out that their coconut water is from a tetrapak (excessively sweet) and the flesh that was added in was also from a very old coconut. Quite disappointing considering it’s meant to be a Thai restaurant - authentic coconut water is a basic. Cmon guys you can do better!

Extremely Disappointed with the Staff and Management at Anytime Fitness Tampines Mart

I’ve never experienced such poor customer service at a gym until I signed up here. From the very beginning, the Malay male staff who handled my registration was rude, dismissive, and seemed completely uninterested in assisting. It already felt like I was being judged just for being there.

When I tried to request a respectful termination of my membership, I was met with even worse treatment over the phone. Rara, another Malay staff member, was condescending, disrespectful, and completely lacking in basic courtesy. The way she spoke was offensive, and the attitude she displayed made it very clear that the gym has zero regard for customer service—especially if you’re not who they want to treat well.

What’s even more disappointing is how obvious it is that this gym treats people based on how they look. If you’re conventionally attractive, you’re treated with smiles and attention. If not, you’re talked down to like you don’t matter.

Even Virgin Active, a far more premium gym, didn’t treat me like this when I chose not to renew my membership. They handled it with professionalism, respect, and class—something this outlet clearly lacks.

Avoid this place. The management needs serious retraining, and the staff culture—especially those mentioned—needs to be re-evaluated. This gym is giving the Anytime Fitness brand a bad reputation.
Nice environment and helpful staff!

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text: The amount of tendon given for the price is ridiculous! No next time.

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text:
This is definitely a must try noodle shop. There are 8 type of noodle cut to choose from, ranging from very thin to fat and broad.

Whats even better, you can refill your noodles unlimitedly if your order a large portion. The refilled noodles can be of any noodle cut. If you are a big eater, you definitely have the chance to try all 8 of them.

If both of you are small eaters and decided to share a big bowl, you can also refill but refill one time only.

I personally like the dry version and the chilli taste great. While the noodle came with soup, you may also separate the noodle from the soup with another bowl and season the sauce yourself using their given chilli and vinegar. Try until you got your perfect proportion.

Definitely will be back. And try their plum juice again.

Business Name: Tongue Tip Lanzhou Beef Noodle 舌尖尖 (Downtown East)
Review Text:
I don't often do reviews but i am doing this review because I have not met any better service from any other stores except this one at pasir ris ehub.  The service people( 2 Malay boys) are exceptional in their service. They are very good, it feels like they are hotel trained. Their service will make your day and make you feel really happy and treasured that you made the choice to dine with them! I must compliment their good service and work ethics! They are also very kind. An elderly entered the store and they accommodated to their needs despite a full service and only 2 front staff. Fantastic work!

One of the things that have stood out to me the most about your gym is the spacious and inviting environment. The gym is always clean, well-maintained, and has plenty of natural light that creates a positive and energizing atmosphere. The open layout and high ceilings make it easy for me to move around and complete my exercises without feeling cramped or confined.They also have an impressive selection of the latest machines and tools. Exceptional customer service. Staff and personal trainers are always friendly and helpful. Fantastic gym environment that helps everyone to achieve their fitness goals.

Been ages since i’ve been to this outlet . Newly renovated . Still the most fully equipped outlet i’ve been . They provide individual sanitiser n towels at the machines . There’s also deodorant and charging ports. Other outlets really need to learn from this outlet. Too bad I don’t stay nearby.

Review Text:
Food is generally good but waited close to an hour for this bitter gourd egg dish…
Came around 7 and the place was only about more than half filled with a few empty tables. After ordering, first dish/skewers ordered only arrived on our table after 25 minutes and following up with the service staff. By this time it was probably peak dinner time and the place was filled and there were also a lot of delivery orders. Finished eating and still had to wait another 10 minutes for our 辣子鸡 and rice. After we finished eating, we thought of just leaving because we’d already finished the rest of our food including our rice. Then the egg dish arrived around close to an hour after we placed our order…

We’ve been to this outlet a few times and it usually doesn’t disappoint. Would still recommend to others but maybe skip or avoid peak meal times…

Review Text:
My 4th Lauwang outlet visit — Prev Serangoon Central, Tampines 1, Bugis+.

Punggol Oasis's outlet is conveniently located just beside Oasis Punggol LRT stn (East Bound, 2 stops from Punggol Central). On the first storey.

However, the service here was just.. fine. It wasn't really peak dining hours. But initially I was waiting to be served a table. So I was in the queue. But wasn't attended to. So I had to walk in & get myself a table as the customer infront was just in the way.

I also find the luo han guo beverage at this outlet a little sweeter. As compared to Bugis+ 's.

After ordering the food & payment online, less than 6-7 mins, the food arrived. Impeccable speed.

The Punggol Settlement is a row of food establishment that lined the coastline of Punggol's Northern region of Punggol Coast. Amidst the towering HDB BTOs nearby, this venue is the best place to unwind after a long day of work and just chill. The best part is it is close to SIT Campus of Punggol Coast and Punggol Coast MRT. Buses 84G and 84W serve this area.

Head to their 7-Eleven Convenience Store and get the Wall's Vanilla Choux Puff at the Ice Cream coolers and double it down while sitting at one of the promenade's open-air public seating. The choux Puff is chewy and the vanilla ice cream interior burst with flavours.

There are a variety of food options there, chinese food, seafood restaurant, BBQ, and a bar. We went there during Saturday night and it was super crowded. Luckily we managed to find a parking space amidst the limited lots. We chose the House of White Bee Hoon restaurant and the service was terrible. The restaurant could not handle the number of orders and missed our table. They only served us drinks, 2 dishes and stopped. We have to keep reminding them about our order and in the end it took 30mins. The indoor & outdoor dining makes no difference as the aircon is equivalent to non-existent. It will be the first & last time for us.

I’ve visited Whisk & Paddle a few times and every dish I’ve tried has been consistently great! The mac and cheese is a must-try — rich, creamy, and surprisingly good. I also recently tried their cream cheese garlic bread, and I’ll definitely be coming back just for that.

What I love most is the location — it’s right next to the park connector, so it’s the perfect spot to chill and have brunch after a morning run.

The only small downside is the indoor temperature. The staff mentioned they leave the glass door open because of people coming in and out, but I couldn’t quite understand the purpose of having a glass door then — isn’t it meant to help keep the cool air inside? It did make the indoor area feel a little warm during my visit.

Still, it’s one of my favourite brunch spots, and I highly recommend it!

Kid’s friendly, nice song & environment and good food. Brunch, lunch & dinner favourite place 
Normal meal is about $20-$30, if adding in drinks and desserts, it will be about $30-$40.
Had the lamb shank while my dad had the pork ribs both were delicious and appealing, the garlic cheese ring was superb. The staff were attentive and prompt, service was great.

Is my second time here after a long time. The place is spacious and cozy. Ordered the dry laksa pasta that is for the SG60.

The sauce is alittle too thick and creamy especially when I was still waiting for my friend food to arrived. And it is little more salty. If it gets cold the saltiness is more obvious. Not sure it my problem, but I cannot feel it is laksa enough, something missing.

Overall, to try something new, is not too bad, but maybe the chef can cook it alittle less salty.

Nice place, nice vibes, mediocre food but expensive! ($50/pax)

Food looked promising, but what we ordered felt and taste average for the price. Portions were decent, but flavours lacked that extra oomph. Not bad, but not particularly memorable either.

Still a good place for a chill brunch.

The oysters were not cold although the shells and plate were full of ice. We assume it would taste fresher and slightly tastier if it is so. The tacos were stuck together with the beef, cheese and some salsa. It was a mess and very hard to consume while we had to seperate each bite with so much difficulty and trouble. It would be better if the beef, cheese and salsa were given individually with the same generous portions. The tacos were so crispy but the combination made it hard to eat and made the tacos soggy. The soup was full of seafood umami and the beef was the highlight of the day. Perfectly medium rare and the meat melted in your mouth. A very example of the chef's grilling skills brought to the heights of culinary. Highly recommended for beef lovers!
Dinner was great. We had a seat near the bar and service was very quick. Photos are with my wife...

Stopped by Whisk and Paddle around 8 PM after a cycling session with my brother. We ordered two Sapporo Lager pints (500ml each at $12). Drinks took about 10 minutes to arrive, and the service was friendly and smooth. Used PayWave with no issues.

Atmosphere was great. It wasn't crowded at that hour, and we got to sit outside where it was calm and relaxing. There was even a live band opposite singing Mandarin songs, which added a nice touch to the evening.

Pet-friendly too. Saw a few people dining outdoors with their dogs, which was nice to see.

Overall a chill spot with good vibes and solid service. On the pricier side, but I’d recommend it for a casual night out or to unwind after a long day.
Food are tasty and they serve scramble egg as an add-on menu which is just right for my child. My kids like the painting and kids' corner.
Dabao kopi from here, they still put in effort for the latte art. Kopi is good also.

A great all times catch-up place with friends and even families especially if you live around Punggol or Sengkang. Away from the city and malls. Enjoy the space, big and open car park and the outdoor scenery ambience.  I enjoy their #wafflewithchicken always. 10 Tebing Lane everyone.

Review Text:

I would like to raise a concern regarding my helper’s experience at your clinic this morning, 27 June 2025.

My helper arrived at the clinic at 7:40 AM, ahead of your opening time at 8:30 AM, in preparation for her scheduled medical checkup. However, once the clinic opened, she was rejected for the checkup and was told she would need to return on Sunday instead.

When my helper called to inform me, she was told the reason for the rejection was that the male doctor on duty could not perform a blood draw for her, and that a female doctor would only be available on Sunday. I found this explanation puzzling, so I called the clinic myself for clarification.

Despite my attempts to understand the situation, I was only told again that the male doctor cannot take her blood, with no valid explanation provided. I even asked whether the doctor was a trainee (which could explain certain limitations), but was told he was not. I also asked whether a nurse could perform the blood draw, and was informed that the clinic does not have a nurse.

I find this situation extremely frustrating. My helper waited nearly an hour outside the clinic, only to be turned away and asked to return two days later. This feels both inefficient and inconsiderate, especially since no prior notice was given about the limitations of your staff or service.

I would appreciate it if someone could explain why this happened, and more importantly, advise where I can escalate this feedback so that other patients do not face similar experiences in the future.

Thank you for your attention, and I hope to receive a proper explanation soon.
Docto Response good  Chong Skin Ein

Extremely disappointed with the experience at this clinic. I was queueing outside for almost an hour, carrying my very sick son the entire time, waiting for them to open. There was no notice or information posted outside to inform patients about this, which could have easily prevented all this unnecessary waiting and stress, especially for a parent with a sick child. Very poor communication and absolutely unacceptable.

weird dr weird clinic. They dont seems to bother with the reviews anyways so let just be true. Visited few days back when unwell, front desk still ok ok. My family and I have been visiting this clinic for years. We understand that the waiting time is long but we were ok with it, as long as we are able to get treated. The doctors are generally nice, patient and thorough when we consult them. The counter staff were ok in general. However, my recent experience in this clinic was disappointing. The counter staff was extremely rude and impatience. I politely asked a question about collection of medication (we waited for at least 20-30 mins already but still not called upon to collect) but received the following unpleasant responses:
- Wait... Can you wait? Wait for few minutes... Just wait...
- I am very busy. You just have to wait... Doctor still need to XXX
- Doctor, can you XXX, the patients are complaining already
We understand that the counter staff may be busy (by the way there are 2 counter staff). As patients/family members, we do not want to make things difficult for the staff. What we wanted from the counter staff was that our responses to be answered politely, and be respected. I sat inside the clinic and observed that this counter lady, for every question that patients asked, her responses would be very hostile and rude, and unpleasant. One patient claimed that he was asked to come down to the clinic at 10.30am, but this counter rudely responded "No, I did not said that (x2)". The patient left the clinic, probably feeling why he was treated that unpleasant way when he was already sick.

All in all, doctors are good, but the system in terms of registration and medication collection needs to be improved. What is more important is, the counter staff (working on 26 Dec morning), needs to work the way she responds to patients. If every patients that asked you a question and you need to be so reactive, defensive, hostile and rude, then the problem lies with herself. She is busy, the clinic is busy, but so are we. Please give us the respect that patients deserve when we visit the clinic.

Registered at 8:30am but the doctor is not in till close to 9:30am and the first queue number haven’t even been called. The worst clinic ever. If doctor cannot come early, then say clinic open at 9:30am.

Admittedly, the wait time is long.
I waited about 1.5h from queue number 60 to 65. My consult was pretty short as it was just a minor sickness, but some queue numbers took a very long while.
And I think that does signify that the doctor is thorough. The locum I saw was pleasant and kind.

I called up the clinic and the nurse told me they have already accepted the numbers of patients for the morning session.

It so amazing, first time i hear from clinic they still got number of patients to meet per session. The nurse just simply want to knock off on time at 2pm.

My daughter had the pleasure of being treated by Dr. Chong Seik Ein at Pioneer Medical Centre, and I couldn't be more impressed. Dr. Chong combines extensive medical knowledge with a compassionate approach, making every visit both informative and comfortable. Her attention to detail and dedication to patient care are evident in every interaction. The entire staff at the centre is also courteous and professional, contributing to a positive overall experience.  Saw many reviews regarding the long waiting time, I felt that it was worth the wait. A good doctor can make the illness feel half cured, and Dr. Chong embodies this philosophy perfectly. Waiting at A&E is even longer unless for emergency cases. This is my third time visiting this clinic. This is close to my home, so I come back here. Except for the doctor's diagnosis, everything else is very bad. The last two times I came, many people had to wait at least 2-3 hours to register. Even after seeing the doctor and waiting to get medicine, they had to wait at least 20-30 minutes. Alas, if you need to wait for a long time, you can inform the patient in advance. Today I came to see a doctor. There were only three people waiting, but I still waited for more than an hour before it was my turn to see a doctor. It's really ridiculously slow and a waste of time. Inefficient. Good find! It’s very homey and gives such a good feel. I liked their food as well. Very few or barely no tourists. Only locals. However there is no lake or water view it’s all blocked by vegetation. So if you’re going for the view there is none. But still  nice place. They have toys for little babies too and they can play while adults eat.

While the service during our visit was fine, I unfortunately experienced severe gastroenteritis shortly after the meal. I strongly suspect the issue originated from the mushroom bruschetta, which appeared off in taste and texture. Out of the four pieces served, I consumed three, as my family did not enjoy them, and I felt compelled to finish the plate.

By the following Monday, I had no appetite, suffered diarrhea over 20 times throughout the day, and experienced severe vomiting (7 times). I even fainted twice due to dehydration and weakness. The vomit clearly contained undigested pieces of the mushroom bruschetta. In addition, the pizza we ordered was undercooked in the center, which further raises concerns about kitchen safety standards that evening.

I am not attaching photos or medical documents to this message, but I will gladly provide all necessary evidence and medical reports if needed for further investigation.

Please take this seriously and look into what may have gone wrong with the food preparation that evening. Food safety should always be a top priority, and I hope appropriate actions will be taken to prevent this from happening to others.

Looking forward to your response.

Sincerely,

Visited with a group of 9 and had a really disappointing experience. There were many empty tables, but none that could accommodate our group size — so we ended up waiting for a table in a restaurant that wasn’t even full.

One of the available tables had finished meals with personal belongings left behind, but the family was nowhere in sight — they were clearly done eating and had gone to queue for a face painting event organised by the restaurant. We asked the manager if we could be seated there or if he could help move the unattended items so we could sit down.

He refused, saying there’s no time limit for diners and nothing could be done. Instead, he just told us to keep waiting, without giving any idea of when the family would return. Meanwhile, he stood from a distance, watching us and appearing smug and indifferent, offering no further help.

The lack of professionalism, flexibility, and basic courtesy was really disappointing — especially since this place used to be much better. Sadly, it’s not somewhere I’d return to or recommend after this experience.

do not be in healthcare industry if you lack basic empathy. Counter staff in her 30s were extremely rude, shouted at my elderly grandma. We spend money to see doctor because we are ill, not to be scolded. Come at your own risk.

I was told by one of the clinic assistant at 615pm that the doctor would be available at 7pm, with my turn likely around 8-830pm. This is frustrating, as if the clinic had answered my call earlier and issued a queue number, I could have gone home to have dinner, shower, and return on time. Instead, I had no choice but to wait at the clinic, as going home would have been too rushed and risked missing my turn.

I attempted to purchase medication but was met with unhelpful and poorly trained auntie staff who was unable to advise me on suitable options based on my prescription history. The lack of professionalism and competence from the clinic assistants is deeply disappointing.

I have decided not to return to this clinic and will lodge a formal complaint with the MOH and inform the area MP. Patients deserve better service and proper training for clinic staff to avoid such inconveniences.

If you’re looking for poor diagnosis, wasted time, and rude customer service, this clinic is the place to go.

I had the unfortunate experience of visiting this clinic twice in 2024, both times being consulted by Dr. Goh.

1.	August 2024 – I sprained my thumb, and the pain extended to my wrist. I explained that I couldn’t move my thumb, and my wrist was in significant pain. Dr. Goh briefly examined my wrist and simply stated that it was sprained. He prescribed ointment, but the pain worsened over the next week. I later visited a polyclinic where the doctor provided a more thorough assessment, diagnosing a nerve injury in my wrist that required a steroid injection. After being referred to a hospital and receiving the injection, I recovered fully within three days.

2.	September 2024 – I experienced heavy menstrual bleeding for two weeks. Dr. Goh advised me to take Norethisterone for 20 days to stop the flow. When I asked if it was necessary to take it for so many days, he insisted it was. He also added that I should take high blood pressure pills, despite me telling him I don’t have high blood pressure. He tested my blood pressure three times and insisted it was abnormal. I explained that I’ve had low blood pressure most of my life and that the elevated reading might be due to panic after bleeding excessively. He refused to reconsider, claiming that high blood pressure pills would reduce the bleeding. When I tested my blood pressure at home, it was normal.

3.	Patient Privacy Concerns – There’s absolutely no regard for patient privacy in this clinic. Two of the counter staff (packing medication and collecting payments) are respectful, speaking softly when dealing with patients’ personal information. However, the two seated behind the counter never get up and instead shout out patients’ full names, NRIC numbers, house addresses, and phone numbers for everyone to hear. During both of my visits, I witnessed them shouting at elderly patients. On one occasion, an elderly man mentioned it was his first time at the clinic, and the staff loudly responded, “Why must you come here?” I also saw a middle-aged woman buying medication without her physical NRIC. Instead of proper verification, the seated staff simply asked her to recite her NRIC number and proceeded to sell the medication. Isn’t this dangerous? Why isn’t there a proper process in place? People come to the clinic unwell – the least they deserve is respectful treatment.
They have the worst clinic assistance. All the new faces are super rude

Suspected dengue last monday but dr goh dismissed me and refused to address it. Prescribed me antibiotics which to i had an adverse reaction to - stomach was in intense pain. Had to go back to dr tay last wed to get meds for my stomach.. went to poly clinic on saturday due to rashes appearing. It has been a week and not surprised that it turned out i had dengue. Dr Goh not only diagnoised me incorrectly.. he even prescribed me meds that i didn't need which caused a whole new issue.. disappointing

Went to Dr Goh a few days ago and I suspected that I had gotten phytophotodermatitis from googling online but the doctor said its not. So i went to National Skin Centre just for the doctor to confirm that it's indeed phytophotodermatitis LOL

Staff had no idea what they are doing. Asked for nebulizer and the staff mention that they have it but required to see doctor. After seeing doctor, it turns out that they don't actually have a working one. This could have cost a life.

Do not recommend coming if there's emergencies.

Good doctors. Poor poor counter staff service display. Been there for my whole life their service was from bad to worst. Staffs have bad attitude and always show patients their anger face. Talk to them nicely never ever reply in good manners. Young and even the old ones are rude too. Apex Medical boss you need to send them to customer service course or maybe they want a pay rise??

Receptionist say to wait about 1 hour but I was waiting there for 2 hours. Waiting is okay, but the fee they charge also high. I see doctor is about 5mins plus plus, consultation charge is $42 yet include medicine.

Dr Ling is always my favourite doctor but I don't understand why Apex charge so much higher now. Can you imagine paying $80 just for cough?
The nurse said computer spoil for 1 month so no government subsidies and won't have for future too. Is there something wrong that we don't know? Only thing I can think of is something happened that caused government to removed the subsidies for this clinic?

The service was really horrible. Just wanted to take a blood test,and they said I must walked in a 730. The staff perviously told me that I can come an hour later when I called at 730 for a blood test. I went down and the staff was really rude to me and said I cannot take at this timing. What's more is that I came down twice early morning and they rejected me. Really bad stuff service.
Dr Ling是一位很棒的医生，不过他的员工服务态度很差，很没礼貌，如果不是Dr Ling医术高明，我不会去这间诊所。员工的态度需要培训。等她们拿药比看医生还久。

I dare say this clinic's handling covid the best out of the 4 clinics in the area.

They actually had signs out to tell patients when the queue is full (I highly recommend putting Chinese / Malay / Tamil signs too, at the side of the counter facing out to the door. Might help elderly patients and foreign workers who do not know English). This is already a world of difference from another clinic I shall not name, which I waited at for 30 mins yesterday only to be told to head over to the next door clinic and wait for 2.5H, because I'm not company sponsored. (They didn't even put a sign, srsly. Half the queue were not company sponsored.)

They also had special signs for people who self-tested ART positive too. Unlike yet another clinic in the area I shall not name, which claimed to do Swab tests online but turned me away in person saying 'no swab test here', APEX is legit. They understood the need when I told them I'm ART positive. They accommodated me when I asked if I could be given a queue no. for couple of hours later, despite the queue being full. Sure their phone line may be down, but their in-person service definitely benefits from that.

Service-wise, the staff were most efficient and polite, and I'm really thankful to Dr Tay, who cracked a joke when she saw how sombre I was about getting covid. The brave lady did not even bulk when I pulled down my mask, despite my fear of transmitting Covid to her. Kudos to her!

If there is one complain I do have, it would be the signage out at the front. It's good that APEX gets along so well with the Universal Dental Group that they even share similar letter fonts, but at first, I didn't dare go in thinking I might end up strapping myself in for a teeth drilling session. Now's not the time for sure, but in the future, when Covid does lighten up, hopefully the clinic will consider rebranding with different letter fonts, if not add an Upstairs and Downstairs Arrow logo alongside the different establishments.

Review Text:
Payment:
Message from NIE said that the complusory health screening is free. However, before any screening is done, I was asked to pay $55. The staff said that they had informed NIE about the miscommunication. Payment cannot be made by VISA as their machine is down.

Procedure:
Before the health screening, we had to print out a form to fill in physically. It's quite long, detailing not just our personal medical details but also our family's medical history. During the screening, the nurse fill in another form with the test results. After that, we were ushered to a tablet station to key in everything again digitally, rendering all the hard copies redundant. The digital form is 15 pages long, and the touchscreen is not sensitive, so it took a very long time to key in those information that took a very long time to complete on hardcopy in the first place.

Privacy:
The waiting room for X-ray consists of 2 rows of chairs placed facing each other and in uncomfortably close distance. (Note that females are required to remove their bras and wear only plain T-shirts.) There's a curtain to separate the waiting room from the rest of the clinic, but once we're called for the X-ray, we'll have to go out. (Ladies, you might want to go with a jacket to cover yourself.)

Staff:
The only redeeming factor I guess is the staff. From the receptionists, to the doctors and nurses, everyone is very patient and friendly.
Address: 36 Nanyang Ave, University Health Service Building

Review Text:

Review Text:
My home gym. I’d go around to try out the other AF gyms with high ratings since I signed up end of last year. Feels like the ratings of some of them are solicited but oh well.

This one is deserving though. Everyone in there are like friends and really welcoming. I bumped into Amirah near my home couple of weeks after I signed up and she called out to me by name. Like how did she even remember my name even if she remembered my face after such a short period of time?

The gym is clean, users are mostly friendly and willing to rotate/share equipments. Love that the gym equipments are well maintained.

Male and female bathrooms are separated (rare for Anytime Fitness gyms).

I’m so relieved this is my home gym. Phew.
Clean

Love the ambience at this gym. It’s a safe space and welcoming place  for gym goers , with top notch equipment and wonderful staff.

It’s a pretty spacious gym with quite a big variety of machines that you don’t usually find in other AF gyms.   Place is generally neat and equipment are well maintained. Nice to see that they provide each equipment with sanitizer spray and wipe down towel.

The higher ceiling and natural light from the many surrounding windows add on to the feeling of spaciousness and good energy at this gym.

Very friendly and welcoming staff at the gym too!

The only unfortunate recent development happening ,  the mall is under renovation and reconfiguration, leading to a relocation of nearest escalator further away as well as shrinkage of free space / stretching area.

Great gym overall! The equipment is top-notch, and the vibes/ambiance are really nice. The staff is super friendly, and the service is a solid 10/10. I also appreciated that when I wanted to cancel, they didn’t pressure me to stay, which says a lot about their professionalism. The changing rooms are always tidy and clean. The only minor downside is that they sometimes reply late, but everything else is great.

The staff at the counter is friendly and the place is so well laid out and personalised. The ladies has many items for sharing.

But there is only 1 toilet. Makes waiting for it difficult.

Not my resident gym, but decided to give it a try! The equipment here are well-maintained. Power racks are sufficient with competition-standard barbells. However the free-weights area needs some improvements. Benches and dumbbells are not maintained properly.

I would say this is more of a powerlifting gym (discouraged for regular gym-goers). The lifters here often “hog” the racks, come in big groups, and take LONG rest times. Properly wouldn’t visit this gym again.

Staff here are friendly though! :)

Very nice and clean gym. Well equipped and not very much crowded.

PT Bumi is well experienced, professional and friendly trainer. Highly recommended.

This gym is top-notch with all the latest equipment and amazing personal trainers.
I’m so glad I have it as my home gym!

PT Bumi’s training sessions are incredible and really help me stay focused on my fitness goals.

I would like to express my heartfelt appreciation for the exceptional team at this gym outlet (CCP) Bumi, Shah, Ari, Amirah, Allyssya, and Ana are amazing. Each of them has consistently demonstrated professionalism, dedication, and a genuine passion for creating an excellent fitness experience.

Bumi brings an unparalleled level of energy and positivity that motivates both staff and members. Shah's commitment to ensuring a smooth operation is evident in his reliability and attention to detail. Ari's knowledge and willingness to go above and beyond have been key to our success. Amirah’s warmth and attentiveness make everyone feel welcome, while Allyssya’s organizational skills and cheerful demeanor have been invaluable. Lastly, Ana’s proactive approach and infectious enthusiasm have left a lasting impression.

Keep up the incredible work!

Amirah and Ari at the Changi City Point branch of Anytime Fitness are absolutely fantastic! They are incredibly friendly, helpful, and always go above and beyond to make members feel welcome. Their positive energy has created such a warm and inviting atmosphere in the gym, making every visit a pleasure. Whether you're a seasoned gym-goer or a newcomer, they’re always ready to assist. Highly recommend this gym, thanks to the amazing team!
Good ambience well maintained equipment and very friendly staff
Love the variety of the machines they offer. They even have small plates like 0.5kg. Easier for progression

The gym is spacious, clean and cozy! Im an AF member but I’m not from AF Changi City Point but I think I want to try gymming here next time hehe :)

As much as we love the accessibility of the gym and the friendliness of the gym goers there, we would love it if there was a better system for putting back the weights and for sorting them according to weight (difficult I know but we can hope)!!

I’ve been a member of AF CCP for quite sometime now and I just wanted to leave a review. As I was looking through other gyms’ reviews (because I’d like to see which is more convenient to my next stop for work) and all I see is bad reviews of the gyms such as low maintenance, bad hygiene, etc.

The gym here is amazing. Great use of space. A lot of machines. Not to mention there’s separate toilets for males and females (this is really awesome for a hijabi like me!) Staff are friendly and consistent. I’m not familiar with their names but I can recognise their faces 

Location is good with a view too. A lot of outlet stores. Food varieties as well. Highly recommend to come and visit the gym!

Dr. Loke himself provided exceptional care. His expertise, professionalism, and genuine concern for my well-being were evident throughout the appointment. He took the time to listen attentively to my concerns, thoroughly explained diagnoses and treatment options, and made me feel comfortable asking questions.

Moreover, the clinic's facilities were modern and well-maintained, contributing to an overall positive experience. The entire team, from the administrative staff to the medical professionals, demonstrated a commitment to patient care that truly set them apart.

I highly recommend One Medical Clinic for anyone seeking a reliable and compassionate general practitioner. My experience was nothing short of excellent, and I am grateful to have found a healthcare provider that prioritizes both the physical and emotional well-being of their patients.

Thank you to the entire team for the exceptional service.
