Waterway Point has always been one of those malls that feels both spacious and lively at the same time. Located right next to Punggol Waterway Park, it’s got that rare combination of shopping convenience and scenic vibes — you can literally finish a coffee and be strolling by the water in under five minutes.

The mall itself is bright, airy, and well laid out, with a good mix of retail, dining, and lifestyle options. Whether you’re here for groceries, a quick meal, or a movie, everything is within easy reach. Dining choices range from casual cafes to family restaurants, and there’s even a decent variety of dessert spots for that after-meal treat. I especially like how there are plenty of seating areas, making it easy to take a breather between shops.

What’s really nice is the way Waterway Point integrates with its surroundings — the outdoor boardwalk and park connectors make it feel less like a concrete mall and more like part of the community. On weekends, you’ll see families with kids playing in the open areas, joggers passing through, and couples taking in the riverside sunset.

All in all, it’s not just a shopping destination but a place to unwind, hang out, and enjoy the Punggol waterfront. Whether you’re here to shop, eat, or just soak in the relaxing atmosphere, Waterway Point delivers a complete day-out experience.

During the treatment, the manual extraction process was extremely painful, and the therapist repeatedly complained about the condition of my skin. While I was aware my skin wasn’t in perfect shape, that’s precisely why I sought professional care. To address the issue, I even opted for an additional treatment at an extra cost of $188, hoping for better results.

Overall, the experience was deeply disappointing, especially given the high cost and the lack of professionalism. I would not recommend this place to anyone seeking quality skincare services. Second time here in two weeks, recently discovered this place.  Really enjoy the drive out to Tuas on a weekend night, the restaurant is casual, comfortable, spacious. And prices very reasonable with free parking (with meal).  Definitely will be back!

Beautiful marina views, spacious open-air seating, and friendly service. The Duck Confit was crispy and tender, Lamb Briyani rich and flavourful, and Fish & Chips fresh and golden. Garlic Fries were addictive! Prices are a bit high, but worth it for the quality and setting. Perfect for a relaxing weekend meal.
Waiter MG ‘s service was excellent, he was attentive , helpful, and delightful to interact with.  His service made our dining experience very pleasant indeed !

If you enjoy the thrill of waiting for a reply that may never come, Marina Bistro is the place for you! Reservations are exclusively via WhatsApp — which is a genius idea if you want to practice patience, meditation, and acceptance of silence. No replies? Perfect! Phone calls? Oh, that’s just for decoration. Apologies for replying late? Why ruin the suspense? Truly a masterclass in how to keep customers guessing. Can’t wait to… never try again.
Good food, good environment especially evening time to view sunset, good service especially MG and team. Love to visit this place again.

Food was great, scenery and ambience was great, and service was personable too. The chendol was lovely for the hot weather with rich coconut milk and strong panda flavors. Had a lovely time at this marina bistro. The view was absolutely beautiful, perfect spot to enjoy the sea breeze and scenic vibes. Food was flavorful, and the service was warm and attentive. A nice place to relax and enjoy a peaceful meal by the water.

Even the sides like the chutney and dhal were spot on and complemented the meal perfectly. A must-try for any briyani lover. Will definitely be coming back for more!

Review Text:
I’ve been training at this branch for a while now and it’s easily one of the best gyms in the area. The environment is clean, well-maintained, and spacious — even during peak hours, it never feels overcrowded.

The equipment is modern and comprehensive, catering to all types of workouts — from strength training to cardio and functional exercises. Machines are always in good working condition, and any maintenance is attended to quickly.

What really sets this gym apart is the team. The staff are friendly, professional, and always ready to help. Whether it’s assisting with equipment, answering questions, or just offering a warm greeting, their positive energy makes a big difference.

It’s also a huge plus that the gym is open 24/7 — super convenient for those with busy or irregular schedules.

If you’re looking for a supportive and clean environment to work out in Jurong, I highly recommend giving this place a try!

Review Text:
My first AF gym, and still the best AF gym I've been to. It may not be the biggest but it makes up for it with a wide variety of equipment that ensures you'll have a well rounded workout. The provision of free towels is something that's spoilt me — now I'm always looking for towels in other gyms. 

And of course, big shout out to the team here at d'Arena. I've yet to go to an outlet with staff that is this friendly and welcoming. Review Text:
My initial experience was great. I’ve heard horror stories of members who had issues cancelling their membership with other AF branches and was assured it wouldn’t happen here. I signed up for 18 months and was relatively happy throughout, the people are nice. However, when it came time to cancel my membership, they kept delaying their response and didn’t want to furnish me with the form to confirm the cancellation. I was constantly asked to go down to their gym and asked why I wanted to cancel (when I had already given my reasoning a few times both on text and in person). After much chasing I finally got the cancellation form and was assured that January will be my final billing month.

Today (1st February) my credit card was charged and I am appalled at the service of this gym. I’ve reached out to their team and hope their service recovery will redeem them.

Just to be clear, AF is great if you have no intentions to leave. It’s only problematic when you try to cancel your membership. I have been highly dissatisfied with the cancellation process and communication hence the low rating.
Address: 511 Upper Jurong Rd, #02-05 Anytime Fitness D'Arena

The layout and ambience are very pleasant and relaxing. Thanks for their blue and white theme. Today, I tried their all day breakfast and my wife chose their signature fish and chips. You won't be disappointed. We also tried their Americano coffee. It is very nice and flavourful. Overall the food is great and highly recommendes.

Free flow plain water in this day and age? What’s not to love!

Jokes aside, ordered their signature fish and chips for lunch and i was quite surprised by its portion. Two huge pieces of fish that would have passed for two servings in other restaurants, well seasoned fries and a side of salad, honestly value for money. The fish was fresh and the batter crispy. Will definitely be back to try the other items

Food came fast. Fried chicken was nicely deep fried with crispy skin. They are generous with their fries. Shoestring fries fried till golden brown and well seasoned. Crispy on the outside and fluffy on the inside. Super addictive. Softshell crab burger was also very good. The rich, silky and sweet cameralised onions add a magical touch to the burger. However, the Softshell crab Pasta was not as good. The batter was thick and doughy, (refer to photo) which made it surfeiting. Lychee Earl Grey was refreshing though I would prefer it less sweet.

Good food & service and have a nice place.

A cozy find at Punggol Coast Mall!

White Cloud Cafe offers a simple and easy-to-understand menu, with prices comparable to most cafes in Singapore. One great perk for dine-in guests is their 20% discount on mains during weekdays from 10am to 5pm, which makes it even more worthwhile. They also have a student meal set at $13.50, which includes a main and a drink.

My daughter ordered the Cajun Pork Chop, which came with a generous portion of salad and mashed potatoes, and a complimentary iced Coke as part of the student meal. I went for the Baked Haddock Fish Fillet served with sautéed mushrooms in garlic and mashed potatoes.

Their mashed potatoes truly stole the show — ultra smooth, creamy, and buttery. I rarely finish mashed potatoes, but I cleaned the plate this time. A close second would be the sautéed mushrooms, which were packed with flavour and nicely done with minced garlic.

A pleasant spot with decent food and thoughtful weekday deals — definitely worth a try if you’re around the area!

The food was delicious, fried chicken and truffle fries were crispy, the chicken chop was beautifully presented, and the polite and attentive staff made the dining experience even more pleasant.
I tried the lemon meringue and it was absolutely amazing - the balance of sweet and sour was just right. Paired with a cup of fragrant Earl Grey tea, it was simply amazing!

The fries and nugget are standards u can get when u do it yr own with frozen ones at home. Carbonara was pretty standard too. Nothing to rave about.

Service was prompt and good though. $80 there about for 3 adults, one child and a toddler. Din felt like it was worth that price. Maybe because we din order the chicken chop. :(

Go there only if u don't use toilets or don't mind smelly toilets sprayed with overpowering artificial fragrance. Water level at the tap is so slow flowing it makes me wonder if the mall mgt does not pay their water bill.

Visited this café for dinner and unfortunately, the entire experience was underwhelming and far from what I expected for the price point.

The Teriyaki Chicken Pizza served was clearly a frozen base with some meat simply added on top.
Something I could have made at home with minimal effort.

For the Chicken and Waffle, the waffle tasted like it came straight from the freezer, the chicken had that dry, air-fried texture and the egg was completely bland with no seasoning at all.

The Mushroom Soup was by far the most disappointing dish. It somehow tasted worse than canned soup, with an odd bitter aftertaste that made it hard to finish. The garlic bread was just a hard piece of bread with some garlic bits sprinkled on top. No flavour, no creaminess. Nothing redeeming.

To make matters worse, the prices were on the higher end. For the quality we received, it simply felt like we were being overcharged. I honestly left feeling like I wasted my money and I believe a refund would be fair considering the poor quality of the meal.

Not a place I’ll be returning to or recommending.

Review Text:
It was our first visit to SOD at Ci Yuan CC, and also our first time trying this café when we were craving a hearty guacamole soft bread breakfast. The portion was generous, the taste delightful, and the price reasonable.

The café has a cosy, neighbourhood charm, not large, but comfortable enough. It opens at 11am, and within half an hour, the crowd starts to fill the place. The ventilation is excellent with no lingering cooking smell, and the aircon is perfectly cool for a relaxed breakfast.

Highly recommended if you are looking for a comfortable spot to enjoy a hearty, satisfying start to your day.

Review Text:
[SOD Cafe]
 9/10
 Ci Yuan CC
 Expected damage $15-$25

Value for money and no service charge. This place has been around for a long time and their serving is huge for their prices. My personal recommendation is their mentaiko pasta with the fried chicken. The sauce makes the pasta very savoury which goes well with the crispy chicken. Wanted to try their soft shell crab mentaiko pasta but they only serve it at the upper thompson branch.

The mentaiko Mac N' Cheese is very decadent due to the heaping amount of cheese which caters to many young cheese lovers. Fried chicken and waffle was good and a go-to for those craving a sweet and savoury meal once in a while.

The dessert - devils chocolate cake, is the icing on the cake as it was so thick and sinful. When paired with the ice cream, you are guaranteed to be seeing a doctor soon which is the job of a good dessert. Definitely recommend this place
Address: 51 Hougang Ave 9, #01-03 Community Club, Ci Yuan Community Centre

We went to the doctor thrice in the past week.
The teacher didn’t even ask the parent of the culprit (a boy who is notorious in the class) to stay behind after class to speak to us. This is unacceptable.
We understand that this matter has been reported to KBCC but after one week- nobody has bothered to reach out to us to even follow up and see whether we need any assistance. Either they are too busy or such accidents happen so often that there’s no cause for alarm even when children’s eyes are injured while attending classes at this CC.

Visited the badminton courts at Woodlands Galaxy Community Club on 5 April (7:30–9:30 PM) and had a terrible experience. There is a female Indian staff member (likely a cleaner or facility attendant) who was extremely rude and aggressive throughout our session.

She was yelling at everyone in a loud and hostile tone, accusing us of placing items around the court that we didn’t even touch. Her behavior was completely uncalled for and made the environment feel tense and unwelcoming. To make things worse, she shouted at us to leave two minutes before our session officially ended, just so she could close up early. We paid for the court and expected to use it peacefully till the end, not to be rushed and yelled at.

This is supposed to be a community facility for everyone – children, the elderly, and families – to enjoy an active lifestyle in a safe and friendly space. Instead, we were made to feel like a nuisance.

Honestly, not a conducive or welcoming place at all if this is how patrons are treated. Proper staff training is clearly lacking here. I’ll also be raising this to relevant channels because our community deserves better – at the very least, some basic respect and professionalism from staff.

Had an absolutely awful experience at the community center today (March 1, 2025, around 10:30 AM). I had the misfortune of interacting with an extremely rude and unhelpful staff member – an Indian lady who was not only unprofessional but also downright dismissive.

We approached her politely to ask for information about an upcoming award ceremony. Instead of offering any assistance, she grumpily told us she didn’t know, her manager wasn’t around, and she couldn't check anything for us. When we asked about the location, her response was simply “don’t know,” with no effort to help us further.

It's shocking that a community center, which is meant to help residents, has staff members like this who seem to have no interest in doing their job properly. Even the Minister would never treat residents with such disrespect. I truly hope the center takes action to investigate and ensure this staff member doesn’t continue to spoil its reputation. Not the level of service I expected at all.

Didn’t expect myself to commit to F45 after ending my 2 weeks trial. For someone who don’t exercise at all, I was really nervous especially during the first lesson but Coach Dhyaanesh and his team gave me a warm welcome with demonstrations for every lesson. They are very professional and will keep a look out on you to ensure that you are able to keep it up. If you are looking for somewhere to try out F45, please visit F45 Jurong West! Their 2 weeks trial is really affordable and worth your time and money!

If you're looking for a motivating environment to push your limits, F45 is the place to be! From the moment I walked through the door, I felt welcomed and supported by the coaches. The workouts are energizing and varied, keeping things fresh and challenging every session.
The coaches are exceptionally knowledgeable and patient too. Coach Dhyaanesh took note of my injury before the session began and modified workouts to make sure I don't further injure myself. I've experienced fantastic improvements in my strength and endurance and I always look forward to my workouts. Thank you, F45 for making fitness fun!

I’ve been a member of F45 Jurong West for almost a year. This is my 4th F45 and my favourite F45 club. The owner and trainer Dhyaanesh is very kind and a great trainer. Shami the other owner and in charge of admin is very responsive. They have other amazing trainers like Jay and Aiz who always fast to assist and give positive feedback and push you during your session as well.
F45 JW also organise gatherings as well for time to time to interact with other members as well.

It's been a real pleasure working out at F45 Jurong West Dhyaanesh and his team are always the best in supporting ensuring you're training safely and also making sure you're challenged during your workout! Looking forward for more session!

刚结束完健身，来给F45一个评价，这是我第20次课了，所以才来给一个负责任的点评

整体：5星好评，强烈推荐！！
先讲下我个人情况，我有断断续续2年健身史，有骨盆前倾，有脊柱侧弯， 尝试过BFT，尝试过私教，尝试过普拉提，这家F45是目前很满意的！

具体说下：
教练：
这一点我很看重！这里的3个教练都很Nice尤其是Dhyaanesh, 不会像有的私教课续完了就心不在焉。每节课教练都会很积极的观察每一个学员，我某个动作做着困难腰疼，他会主动过来教我一个适合我的动作变式，有的学员有氧很累蹲地下休息，他会过来问询，给拿糖果防止低血糖，能记住每个学员有什么禁忌和伤病，在相应的动作时作出提醒，防止受伤！
我个人觉得在教练这一块子做的真的非常好！甩大部分团体类健身一条街！（我第一次去BFT做阻力训练……都是30KG的重量…地下有20的片……也没人关心你能不能推……我连换都换不动……干看着……就真的很离谱）

位置：
在比较西边了，但是很便利，楼下一个食阁一个shengsiong, 健身完了买点菜就很顺手～

设备：
基本上该有的都有了，不算特别新，但我觉得够用了，每节课的设置都不一样，有有氧，有阻力，有Hybrid，配合大器械，小器械和一些自重训练，反正每天不会重样，不会腻歪！

总结下我觉得很好的形式，很用心负责的教练，你只需要负责过去，剩下的就跟着节奏来，教练会指导也会鼓励，一闭眼就结束了～～对于我一个弱鸡来讲效果不错，我现在也是一个壮起来的人了！到了需要重新买运动装备的程度哈哈！

Tried going for the F45 challenge(45days). Trainers in this outlet is good, classes were effective.

Strongly recommend if you would like to get to a healthy lifestyle. The key is to turn up for classes everyday and leave it for the program to shape you.

Thankful for the season at F45 Jurong West. My spouse and I are very grateful for the patience coaching by Founder/Coach Dhyaanesh, Coach Aziz, Coach Jay etc during our time there. Both of us didn’t have fitness background and starting the fitness journey were intimidating for us but the team of dedicated and experienced Coaches and F45’s thoughtful workout design for strength and cardio made it easy for us to follow through. It’s really fun and motivating that the classes change every 4 weeks. You never have to worry of getting bored. We were usually at the morning 7.15am and the evening 7.15pm or 8.15pm classes. We enjoyed the quietness of morning and the busyness of evening classes. The clean shower room was important for me when I attended the morning classes before work and the best part is it’s usually unoccupied.

While we decided to pause our fitness journey with F45 fitness this season due to my spouse’s work schedule, we would love to be back in near future.

Highly recommended for you if you’re on the verge of making a decision. You can try them for 2 weeks trial first.

Pro-tips :
1) Don’t stop after 1 session, push through the sessions and your aches and sores would feel less intensive. For us, we kind of recovered after 3 consecutive days of classes when our muscles adapted.

2) Do what your Coaches told you. We were often in Coach Dhyaanesh and Coach Jay’s classes, they were really helpful to correct us or show us modified workout when they saw us struggling.

3) Ask the Coaches if you’re sure. During one of the busy classes, I remember feeling unsure how I should hold the weight and I was glad I asked Coach Aziz. It was important for me I picked up the right habits.

4) Go slow and focus on form when you’re new. We are glad we learnt our foundation from them.

Thank you, Coach Dhyaanesh and F45 Jurong West!

Oh yah, there’s a Sheng Siong supermarket and a coffeeshop nearby. Very convenient!
The best gym I have ever been to. Awesome gym buddies and coaches. It is not those standard gym but a community where everyone get together to have fun and train to keep fit.

I have been going to F45 Jurong West for more than half a year and I love the classes, the coaches and the community. The classes have really helped with my weight loss journey and I love that every class is always different!

My time at F45 Studio has been exceptional. The studio's ambiance is welcoming, the coaches are professional and friendly, and the pricing is reasonable. It's a top choice for anyone seeking effective workouts and a supportive environment. Highly recommended!

Joined the studio in Sept 2023 and have been loving it so far. The workouts are fun and if you stay to your goals, you will be able to lose some weight and gain muscles like I do.

The coaches are very friendly and they are always around to push/motivate you when you need it. There are many different classes timings that will definitely catered to your needs too. I have personally attended morning, afternoon and the night classes.

F45 Jurong West has a very inclusive environment. I brought my elderly parents to work out with me and despite them not being able to fit in, the team was so patient and ever-ready to make my parents' fitness experience a safe, effective, pleasant and memorable one. Thank you to each and every one of the coaches! We hope to be back soon.

Joined last Aug, never look back since.
Coach: Dhyaanesh led a team of wonderful coaches.
Difficulty: The work out can be modified for anyone.
Location: Near coffeeshop and Shengsiong, but I suggest you stay away
Price: It depends how often you go  Maximize it by attending everyday
Overall: I improved my BMI, fitness level and overall wellness after joining.

Super glad I embarked my fitness journey with F45 JW. There’s a place for everyone here - regardless of your fitness level! Trainers are extremely encouraging and patient + studio size is very decent.

Great location for westies since you can get your grocery fix right after the session!

Very helpful coaches who guide and encourage us according to our individual abilities. No stress workouts! Best for beginners like me, rusty from years of inactivity, and afraid to enter a gym!  F45 Jurong West has the friendliest coaches and workout buddies!

I been to ~10 fitness centers since last year and was trying to find a good place to commit long term. It is this place man. Super worth it in terms of price.

The coaches here are 10/10. They are all supportive, instructive and encouraging.

The equipments are we kept and facilities clean. Air conditioned.

Oh it's also above the Sheng Shiong supermarket and beside a food court. So I usually time my groceries shopping when I go for a session.
Really friendly and knowledgeable trainers and owner/trainer. Loved my experience there!

I work around Tuas. Broth is slightly too sweet for me, and duck slightly tough. It is a normal bowl of kwap zap. Will not make a special trip for it next time but definitely a hearty bowl for those who works nearby!
Very nice. Must try!
Must eat !!!
Not easy to get good food in Tuas South!! This is a good reason to come to Tuas.
Duck rice and chilli is nice. Worth to come here to eat

Both uncle and aunty was all smiles and very polite. We love how thinly sliced the duck was and the broth was light, herbalicious, clear and delicious. We enjoyed every bit of it. Thank you for the sumptuous breakfast!

Authentic old school braise duck flavours, they use yam to cook their braise duck rice which is rare nowadays. I've tried the braised duck rice, noodles and kway chup. The surprising take away is they have very good soup, it's super tasty, I asked for refills and owners were more than happy to give you more refills. Very good service and owners also asked for feedbacks for further improvement from customers. Will recommend anyone to go give it a try.
Very delicious duck rice, the braised meat is very flavourful .  Store owners very friendly and polite . Would definitely come back again
Surprised to have good duck rice in this food court in Tuas. I added large intestines and paid 7.50 and it’s worth the price.

The trainers were extremely patient and helpful. I had my reservations to join F45 as I was concerned that the workouts would be too fast paced. However, the trainers ensured that I paced myself and started slow to get my body accustomed to the trainings. The trainers were also very knowledgeable and were always on the lookout to ensure that your form is proper. Gotta say, i've no regrets signing up!

Pricing was definitely a big consideration factor at first but after going to the classes for a month, the value definitely comes from having a room full of equipment set up according to the day's planned workout. So all we gotta do is to make sure we turn up, get a good sweat and get out of there. And the exercises are different every day, so there is a good mix up to keep us guessing and scare before our next session. 

Can we do HIIT ourselves? We could but it is more fun with more variations that include kettlebells, bar bells, rowing machines and exercise balls. 

4 weeks into our F45 Challenge and I am glad to have started this journey with my buddy.

He is strong and consistent. Always pushing me hard and encouraging me in our sessions. The coaches as well. While they are not those hellish trainers from BMT, they do challenge you and the onus is on us to take their souls David Goggins' style and push through.

It is good that @f45_training_jurongwest is near to both of our homes, so it was convenient to check in, get the work done and get back to both of our families and lives.

So glad a studio opened up in the area so there is no excuse to get myself moving!! The owners & trainers are really friendly and eager to help, i have definitely gotten stronger throughout my time training here. Also made some great friends too, truly a great community to be around!
Great, friendly coaches! Really happy that I have found something fun and works with my timing to help me with my fitness journey
This place got me hooked to a workout routine.. great atmosphere.. amazing people.. and excellent coaches... Continue the good work Dhyaneesh and team !

Instructors at F45 Training Jurong West will propose exercises to cater to your fitness level. If you are fit, they will push and motivate you to complete exercises with heavier weights, to achieve better results. If you're struggling, they will come to you and propose alternative workout options that are less strenuous. Very encouraging and nice instructors there. Special mention to Coach Dhyaanesh and Josiah

I ordered the Pork Katsu Curry Rice with an add-on of miso soup and cabbage. The pork katsu was crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, prepared well without any greasy aftertaste. The curry was slightly on the bland side, but it still complemented the rice nicely. Overall, it was a well-balanced meal. I will definitely return for more.
Used to be good. Came back recently and was disappointed that the standard has dropped. Pork katsu was extremely tough and chewy and mostly inedible. Totally not worth the price.

I am surprised I get to eat excellent Tonkatsu open in the coffee shop.

Whatever they served is absolutely restaurant standard, from the Crockery to the food quality and the arrangement. I am sure from the first close look at the food, many will believe that it must be a restaurant.

Taste wise, absolutely hit the mark - Restaurant standard. The portion is also very generous and it is rather affordable too.

Ex-restaurant chef is no joke and it is worthy of its reputation

Was late and worried this stall is closed.  Had gone there at 815pm n was told last order was slightly before 9pm.

Had ordered pork n chicken katsu set that came salad n soup.  Added one side dish of 2 pieces of fried ebi.  Cost almost $33.

Rather pricy for a coffee shop set up but food is of reasonable quality.  Someone reviewed as same as Ma Maison (MM).  Really?

I tapau tonkatsu from MM in JB.  The food is still excellent after 1.5 hours of commuting back to Singapore.  Food stand for that long n still taste good.  That's quality of the food at MM southkey mid valley JB.

Only a short wait at this stall and collected my order in less than 15 mins.  Rather efficient.

Stingy in giving the brown sauce!  I was only given 2 small sauce cups!!  But paid almost $32.  Rather loop sided deal!

May return if I crave for tonkatsu n around this area or don't know what to eat.  Will not be my natural choice to go to this place as the carpark exit did not allow good visibility of cars when trying to filter to the main street.

Excellent Stew, Lamb Shank. Relaxed Atmosphere

Had lunch on 22nd Nov and was reccomended the pork ribs. The outer layer was hard and slightly burnt, the mash potatoes were tasteless and the sauce didn't go well with the ribs. When I informed the waiter about it, he got the cook out to my table and told him 'customer complained about the food' ..
Left disappointed and wondered how the quality of food has deteriorated over the months.

Food is delicious, portions are generous and price is reasonable. Service is also pretty good.
And even though they don't have a kids menu, they are flexible enough to reduce the portion on the normal menu item and just charge half price.
Nice quiet place for lunch with the kids…

Highly Recommended. Delicious Melt-in-your-mouth barbecue pork ribs were the ace special of the day. on the regular menu, the mutton soup is accompanied with this excellent fresh chili sauce and your choice of rice or baguette. Edamame portions are generous. The coconut shakes are fun too. Chill ambience.

Hundred % attentive staff, really good food and enjoyed the vibe here. Recommended to eat Hainanese braised pork trotters and German pork knuckle as well as the BBQ pork ribs. Glad my family enjoyed the food here. Highly recommended to come here

The eatery has both indoor and outdoor seatings. No charge for water. There is a service tax and no GST. Polite Myanmarese wait staff.

For $29.90 you get quite a big serving of Oxtail Stew. You can either choose to have it served with rice or baguette. There were 3 pieces of fairly large ox tail, big potato chunks, carrots and whole onion. The ox tail meat was soft and came off the bone easily.

The chicken curry ($15.90) was surprisingly not oily unlike the ones you normally get served with a layer of oil floating on the surface. It did not have the cloying sweetness of a lemak curry. Strong smell of spices reminiscent of Indian curry. Decent pieces of chicken however disappointed that there was only 1 piece of potato the size of a 50 cents coin.

We ordered hainanese lamb shank, fish and chips and Dory aglio olio for lunch on national day and they were all delicious. Service was great too and they would top up our drinking water glasses regularly (much appreciated). Will definitely return again to try more dishes!
Wonderful food with a beautiful scenery. MG was a really friendly staff and made us smile throughout the meal.

Totally regret ordering the Pizza too told the waitress - I will never order this frozen pizza-  and she simply laugh it off/walk away with no apologies. (bunch of untrained staff)

After reading the reviews decided to give it a try despite the Ventilation problem. Was disappointed that after months of feedback, it was still not resolved properly. The whole place smells oily and my clothes does smell like that after leaving the place.

Then again they are running a business and the cost to rectify this problem may be high hence the reluctance to rectify it.

To each their own, some just brush this off and are less affected by the ventilation.

Googled and found the following recommendation and decided to go ahead to try. Located in a quiet part of the neighbourhood, Reached there just after 2pm and there were no crowds and sitting was not a problem.  We could choose our own sitting.

Cafe was quiet and tables were either studying or having group chats. place is very instragamable. It become more crowded after 3 plus.

Minimum staff interaction which was ordering at counter and being served the food only.

Ordered honey glazed wings, Hawaiian pizza and smoked salmon waffles. Drinks called are latte and hot chocolate. Food was prepared very quickly. Food tasted great and for the portion ordered is just nice. Latte could have done with more milk in my view.

I didn't experience any bad food or service and will revisit again. A last feedback is perhaps to look to change the cushions as some are very stained. Recommended.

Came back.again.to this cafe on a weekday. Saw only 2 staffs working. Understand from one of the staff that they are understaff on.that day. Felt pity of them running in and out ordering.and preparing food. But the service rendered to me was still great.

Their coffee was one of the best.i had before. This will be my frequent place from now onwards.

First time came to this cafe. Definitely a hidden gem. Came on a weekend and pretty crowded. Food were fantastic. Ordered almond croissant and a pizza to share with my friend. Great food ! Service was very attentive no doubt the place was crowded.
Defintely will come back again for more food and drink .

Horrible place! We ordered 4 mains and a side of fries. We left most of the food untouched, and we stank of old oil leaving the restaurant.

Fries were refried. Hard and stinking of old oil.

Eggs were burnt and again stank and smelt of oil oil. Restaurant refried it but it was horrible too. Maybe a filthy pan in the mix?

Picture of the sad ham speaks for itself

Hash brown meal came quickly enough. The cheese and ham came 15mins later, the hard fries took another 20-25mins after

There’s a reason why the place was basically empty
The food is quite good and the atmosphere is lovely. A bit on the pricey side considering the taste, but overall a nice spot for a weekend getaway.
Had the ITW Red Lake berry drink  and the red velvet cake which was nice. Came here on Good Friday night and it was quiet. Last order was 815pm n they closed at 9pm.

Would give more than 5 stars if we could. Had a horrible service at the nearby Italian restaurant and found this absolute gem instead. Love love loved the service and owner was so accommodating. Service was quick and amazing! My toddler spilt my hubby’s coffee accidentally and not only did the waitress and owner help us clean up immediately and check on our baby, they even made us a new cup. Really went above and beyond. We had such a great time, will definitely be back.
The crab pasta and truffle fries were super good! Baby loved them and especially loved the ice cream with the chocolate lava cake.

Many thanks to the staff and owner and see you again soon! :)

I visited with the intent to fill up my immunisation records for overseas exchange, and was denied at Fullerton even though NTU asked us students to go Fullerton to have it filled up. Their excuse was that we need to come before 4pm to do so, even though the clinic closes at 9pm. However, this information was nowhere stated on their website. I even called them before going down so that I could confirm but no one answered the call. Receptionist staff were very rude as well. Many of my friends also have very bad experience with Fullerton Health, including rude and incompetent staff. So NTU if you see this, please consider changing the healthcare provider if you have the slightest care for your students wellbeing.

Bad experience twice with the doctors here. I only come here because it is the closest clinic to the school and it is hard for me to travel when I am sick. The doctors treat patients as if they are faking their illness. It is your job to give good treatment including good service to patients and you are PAID to do so even by those who are faking so what’s with the terrible attitude? If you do not like the job, stop working instead of being annoying to patients. I am already in a bad mood because I am unwell and coming here only makes it worse and the meds do not really help either. It will be great if all the doctors can be changed to better ones that have higher EQ and IQ.

As compared to NTU's other insurance providers like AIA, Fullerton's coverage really isn't good. Insurers like AIA have online platforms to facilitate claims submissions, but Fullerton makes it so inconvenient by insisting on us going to NTU clinic to get a paper form, and to submit paper receipts. Not exactly making it convenient for claims.

The staff here especially elderly ones are very rude. I came in as I booked a vaccine appointment with this clinic the elderly staff Rudely told me to do the declaration form as I presented my IC, the staff didn’t even ask why I am there instead took my ic and told me to seat down.

After I received my 4th booster vaccine, the elderly staff rudely gave me the acknowledgment slip and asked me to go off in a rude manner.

I don’t know whether this staff is having a bad day at work or what but this is not the way to behave toward the patient. I even wonder if this staff is given proper training to learn how to attend to patients especially elderly patients because some of them aren't familiar with the technology.

These staff should be laid off from their job if they aren't happy with their current job because patients are paying their salaries to begin in the first place.

Our daughter has an uncanny ability to identify places to go for meals when we have no idea what is available nearby. We found an unlikely location for one of Maruhachi Donburi Curry branch stall at Block 671 Edgefield Plains! Even when you arrive by Google maps, you can hardly find it as it is located within the Happy hawkers food court under Block 671.
We were quite happy to find food satisfying and of excellent quality. We ordered the Ebi Fry curry rice and their signature Pork Katsu rice set. The Pork Katsu aka Tonkatsu cutlet was fried extra crispy on the outside, but exquisitely juicy amd tender on the side (see photo). It is comparable to those served at Ma Maison outlets, if not better! The miso soup and the cabbage salad topped with Japanese sesame dressing complemented the tonkatsu very well.
I hope Maruhachi will maintain their quality, especially at this outlet. Our meal was super satisfying!

Ordered Black Pork Katsudon. Below average rice quality, pork heavily marinated with black pepper, zero crunch   ( of coz I'm not talking about the part with "an egg" on top). The egg is suppose to accentuate the taste and honestly, there is no taste at all. Perhaps I should order their Teishoku since I'm so fussy . Staff is less than welcoming but not rude. Overworked? I don't know. I'll try at another branch since they have expanded quite a bit. Atmosphere - food court so can't expect too much.

I wish i can meet the manager or the owner and tell them if you really put intention to build this business then please at least train your staffs. Business Name: JING RAN RESTAURANT 第二家园餐馆
Review Text:
Would recommend!

Tried a variety of dishes for dinner. They have a good spread of options, and the flavours striking in a way that speaks to their authenticity while being affordable.

Their dishes were great. The standout was the steamed sea bass, the fish was fresh, the texture was delicate but robust. Their vegetables were well seasoned, with stir fried beans crisp and flavourful. The egg and tomato was a simple dish but was no less satisfying.

Their food also did not shy away in the spice area, with the heat making a balanced roundness to the dishes without being overpowering. For those not well acquainted with spice, I’m sure they are amenable to requests to taper the kick. Though I do recommend it for the experience.

Service was prompt and attentive, complementing the dishes served. Would come again. They also have private rooms with KTV systems.
Address: 511 Upper Jurong Rd, B-01-01 Arena Country Club

Review Text:
Uniqlo Waterway Point: A Great Shopping Experience with Excellent Customer Service (5/5 Stars)

Rating:

• Product Selection: 5/5 (Great selection of Heattech items and other apparel)

• Product Quality: 5/5 (Excellent quality Heattech and comfortable pants)

• Customer Service: 5/5 (Exceptional service from Shyaf and Azrinah, especially Azrinah's patience and style advice)

• Store Ambience: 4/5 (Well-organized and easy to navigate)

Overall: 5/5

I recently visited the Uniqlo store at Waterway Point (83 Punggol Central, #01-21, Singapore 828761) and had a fantastic shopping experience. I was particularly pleased with the selection of Heattech items. I picked up a navy blue Heattech Cotton Crew Neck T-Shirt, an off-white Heattech Cotton Crew Neck T-Shirt, and a pair of black Washable Knit Ribbed Pants (Co-ord) (Regular Length).  The quality of the Heattech is, as always, excellent, and the pants are incredibly comfortable.

The service I received from Shyaf and Azrinah was exceptional. Azrinah was especially patient and helpful, offering valuable style advice as I tried on different items.  Her assistance made my shopping experience much more enjoyable.

The store is well-organized and easy to navigate. I highly recommend this Uniqlo location for its great products and outstanding customer service. I'll definitely be back!

I ordered some lemon tea and egg and waffles for breakfast and the lemon tea was sour BUT there was sugar syrup so I could make it sweet which is how I like it. The egg and waffles however were amazing. The egg was the weakest part but it was still rich and tasty, the waffles however were amazingly crunchy and the honey they provided supplemented this fact more. The cherry on top was the crunchy greens which were just nice with the sauce they used. The workers were cool and the place was well air conditioned and well cleaned with a toilet to add. In conclusion, amazing place, would come back for more.

I had a bad experience at Mamana Kitchen. While me, my son and my sister were dining in to try their breakfast menu, my son accidentally broke the table’s QR code. I informed and offered to pay for the damage when the lady (i assumed was the owner) served our food. However, HALFWAY through our meal, she accused my son of breaking it again, saying that her staff recognized my son and that he already broke it before which is untrue, as we hadn’t visited in over a month and QR codes weren’t even used then.

She insisted it was him despite our explanation, and gave a rude “warning” not to let it happen again. She also said the boy who broke it was at the outdoor seating, with only my son and my husband around. I asked my husband and he said there had been no such incident. She even told us that she would like us to visit again, so although he “broke” twice, we should be more vigilant. The way she gave a smirk, and insisted in her mind that it was my son without checking the cctv or to show any evidence made me extremely furious. When the owner left, I confronted the staff, she mentioned the incident she referred to happened INDOORS, and that clearly telling us that it wasn’t my son as our last visit, they haven’t introduced the QR code yet. The staff immediately apologized. She was helpful, and very apologetic and I was very thankful of that.

Being falsely accused like that, especially mid-meal, was upsetting and unprofessional. I didn’t even get to finish the food as I had no appetite after we got falsely accused. We definitely won’t be returning. Please review your evidence before making such accusations.

Unsafe & Poor Quality Utensils for Children!

Deeply concern & disappointed towards their poor quality of utensils used. The bowl used for my child's spaghetti from the kids meal — was in extremely poor condition!

Look at the attached image - it was so badly scratched that I was genuinely alarmed. Scratched plastic, especially when used to serve hot food, can leach harmful chemicals into the meal. This is particularly worrying given that this bowl was clearly intended for children.

As a proud Singaporean dining in one of our most established tourist attractions, I expect cafés to uphold the highest standards of hygiene & safety, especially when serving meals to young children! The use of such degraded and potentially hazardous tableware is absolutely unacceptable.

Ensuring safe, clean & food-safe materials should be a non-negotiable standard for any food establishment.

Overall, it was a decent experience for zichar, though familiarity with what's good would be ideal.

I have been bringing my daughter to this clinic since she was just 2 months old. As for the counter staff, they are generally kind and helpful. While there may be one who comes across as a little eccentric, it does not take away from the fact that this is a very good clinic. I trust the care provided here, and will continue bringing my daughter whenever we need a reliable and compassionate paediatrician.
Very good in diagnosing. Excellent doctor.

Dr. Goh at KidsHealth Paediatric Centre is very kind and caring. She is consultative, always sharing with us ways to take care of ourselves and what to look out for. We're grateful for her professionalism and dedication shown during every visit!

Her clinic is one of the few paediatric clinics in yishun area, so it is extremely popular and always has a queue. Expect to wait about 2 hours or so during peak periods. Do come early if your child was not well, or have someone queue up first. Bring your stroller along if your child was not well as there's not many seats available.

Iwas looking for children pediatric and found it  in this clinic. I like that doctor explanes everything. Not just this for runing nose, this for caugh and etc. Doctor explaned what it could be. How we are going to treat it. And what I should look at if something go wrong.
There is play corner, so my 2 kids were busy playing while we were waiting our turn.
What I also liked is new renovation and clean place.

I would like to express my deepest gratitude to Dr. Goh for the exceptional care provided to my 2 children since they are born. Dr. Goh has been incredibly helpful and patient throughout our numerous visits. Her extensive knowledge and expertise were crucial in diagnosing and addressing my child’s frequent sensitive airways. Dr. Goh not only solved the problem but also offered valuable advice for ongoing care and prevention. Additionally, her team of nurses has been friendly, helpful, and professional, making our experience even more positive. We are truly thankful for the outstanding medical support and compassionate approach of Dr. Goh and her team.

We had been seeing Dr Goh since #1 was a baby till now (4+yrs old) and #2 also went there even we had moved to east side. Dr Goh is detailed, knowledgeable and patience even her clinic staff. She shared holistic ways of healing and treating too.

We have been seeing Dr. Goh for our first born till now the third child healthcare needs for the past 11 years, and our experience has been overwhelmingly positive. Dr. Goh is not only highly knowledgeable and professional but also remarkably compassionate.

For the front counter nurses, We are grateful for their dedication and the positive impact they’ve had on our child’s care. Their professionalism and kindness make them stand out, and we highly recommend them to any family in need of pediatric care.

We’ve been bringing both our 5-year-old and 10-month-old sons to KidsHealth Paediatric Clinic in Yishun, and our experience has been nothing short of exceptional. Dr. Goh is incredibly kind and caring, always taking the time to address our concerns with patience and clarity. She explains medical matters in simple, easy-to-understand terms, which is so reassuring as a parent.

The front staff, especially Jasmine, are professional and extremely helpful. The clinic's design is thoughtful, with both an air-conditioned waiting area and a spacious open-air waiting area. This segregation is particularly considerate, as some parents may prefer not to stay in an enclosed space when their child is unwell.

I was especially impressed by an instance where I witnessed Jasmine during triage. She quickly noticed that a child had an extremely high fever and immediately checked with the parent to administer a dose of ibuprofen. Her quick action and attentiveness made all the difference.

Overall, KidsHealth Paediatric Clinic offers outstanding care and service. We’re grateful to have found such a wonderful place for our children’s healthcare needs.

From front staff to Dr Goh herself, they have been exceptionally helpful and good. I can see that they work hard to make sure everyone is attended to. And Dr Goh is detailed and knowledgeable. She shared holistic ways of healing and treating too. Thank you

First time visiting this clinic and unfortunately, encountered three very rude staff members. No matter how skilled the doctor, a nurse with an attitude can ruin the experience. This clinic is a lost cause.

Multiple visits here for the past 4 years, being a mom of 3.

Doctor has always been helpful, detailed and patient dealing with queries and cranky children. Medicines works as intended and so far I do not have any experience of follow-up visit because child was still unwell, thankful for that.

Nurses/counter staff, in my experience, have been great. Gentle with my girls, and kind but some doesn't look as approachable. Not an issue though.

The queueing system, however, has not changed for the past few years. Snaking queues, long waiting hours; I had to be "kiasu" enough to reach as early as 7:30am to "chope" my place just to avoid +++ waiting time. Once, we were third in line but had to make way for appointment basis visit, followed by 2 others which took more than an hour to wait (from opening time) — with sick cranky kids it's a chore.

Previously during covid days, the nurses were quite strict on number of people waiting in the clinic (which to me was good honestly given the small space); but on my recent visit, most of the them were waiting inside. It gets a little chaotic though with all the sick, crying kids and tight space. There's some toys prepared for the kids too.

Payable by CDA. Not sure what other payment method accepted.

On better days, I get to have breakfast nearby first while waiting; the nurse will give a call when you're 3rd in line so there's ample time to head back.

I'd recommend for non urgent visits; and if you have more time to spare. Otherwise, GP/polyclinic may be a better option.

Despite all these, my number one choice will still be the GP right across my block for convenience (though we've had 2nd visit issues cause of unsuitable meds). Its much cheaper too. Hahaha.

We visited Dr Goh because our 6 month old still had phlegm after catching a cold almost 3 weeks ago.

Similar to most paediatric clinics that we've visited, KidsHealth accepts appointments and limits walk-ins. They were also very clear that the wait for walk-ins might be 1-2hrs. This was acceptable for us as we have not seen any paediatric clinics with little or no waiting required for walk-ins.

We were thankful for the coffeeshop that allowed us to wait for 2hrs with a full tummy.

Will strongly suggest to visit a normal family clinic if your child is older, or if the symptoms are mild.

My family and I would like to extend our deepest thanks to Dr. Chuang Wei Ping for his exceptional care and attentiveness.

During my father’s visit on 30 April, Dr. Chuang picked up on something subtle and recommended an ECG, something my father hadn’t even thought necessary at the time.

That simple, precautionary step turned out to be life-changing. The ECG revealed clogged arteries, and even the hospital doctors later remarked how lucky it was we came in when we did—just in time to prevent what could have been a major heart attack.

We’re beyond grateful for Dr. Chuang’s sharp eye, medical intuition, and genuine concern.

Thank you, Dr. Chuang.

One easy but wrong way is to throw training at an employee when the harder right is to give him or her the unpleasant but truthful feedback. Few want and dare to do what’s necessary to help others.

Richton Café is a hidden gem conveniently located below an HDB block in Pasir Ris, making it a great spot for a quick and satisfying lunch fix. The café offers an impressive variety of affordable and reasonably priced dishes, catering to different cravings. Whether you’re in the mood for Mee Goreng, Chicken Cutlet Rice, Hongkong Mee, Hor Fun, Mui Fun, Popcorn Chicken, Yong Tau Foo, Fried Bee Hoon, or Kway Teow, there’s always something to choose from.

One of the highlights of this café is its indoor air-conditioned dining area, which provides a comfortable escape from the heat. However, seating is quite limited, especially during weekday lunch hours, so it’s best to come early or be prepared for a short wait. Despite the crowd, the service is efficient, and orders are usually prepared quite fast, making it a convenient option for those on a tight schedule.

A standout for me is their sambal chili—flavorful with just the right amount of spice, enhancing many of their dishes perfectly. It’s the kind of place that serves no-frills, hearty meals, ideal for a casual and fuss-free lunch.

If you’re in the Pasir Ris area and looking for a budget-friendly, tasty, and quick meal, Richton Café is definitely worth a visit!

*However do note that there is no toilet  there but there is hand-wash basin at the side.

I visited a loved one at Outram Community Hospital and was very impressed by the overall environment and care provided. The hospital is clean, modern, and thoughtfully designed, creating a calm and welcoming space for both patients and visitors. Carpark is also well organized with sufficient parking lots.

What stood out most was the professionalism and warmth of the staff — from nurses to therapists to admin personnel. Everyone was patient, respectful, and genuinely caring in how they interacted with the patients. It gave me a lot of reassurance seeing my loved one so well looked after.

Facilities were well-maintained given its newly opened as well and visiting hours were managed smoothly. There are also great amenities - Koufu food court, POSB ATM, AXS machine, starbucks, Koi, and a pharmacy. Pretty decent for a community hospital.

A great example of community healthcare done right unlike some others i have visited. Thank you to the team at Outram Community Hospital for your dedication and compassion.

Don’t tell people to put wheelchair outside hallway for public use when they still need it. You know how hard it is to find another in the other floors beside entrance? If the patients need the wheelchair they would’ve got the chair before they entered.

I visited the hospital with my grandma today and when she went in for her treatment, I waited for her outside and decided to wheel the empty wheelchair to an area with seat.

An older nurse stop me and ask that I placed the wheel chair outside. I said my grandma still wants to use the wheel chair as she’ll only be inside for a short while, but she still insisted I put it outside so everyone can use.

Can you for the love of god use your head and understand the reason why it’s a dumb idea to ask patient to put wheel chair outside the hallway? There is literally no wheelchair outside especially when there is a lot of visitors. Why do you think all of us are bringing the wheelchair with us whenever we go?

If I put it outside “for someone to use” and they take the wheel chair, I need to go all the way to the ground floor because that’s the only place I know where to get wheel chair. If my grandmother alone came here, she put out then how? Can’t find the wheel chair and ask her go all the way first floor to get?? If my grandfather came instead, he need go all the way to the first floor. You only want young people to accompany patient is it?

Trouble another nurse to get wheelchair all the way from first floor? I’m sure they don’t exactly know where to find wheel chairs either in the other floor. It’s near impossible because I also had to find wheelchair in the other floor before.

You know I’m honestly applaud and offended, like if this was my grandmother I don’t think she even knows where to find the wheel chair after she put outside. And is it even necessary to tell us this? If you have limited wheelchairs I understand, but I visited the hospital and there are numerous wheelchairs outside the entrance ground floor. It comes off as a little too insensitive and stuck up. Also why am I the only one who was told this?? She never even tell the other older visitors who are accompanying the patient. When my mother came to me she immediately stop what she said and left?? Just because I’m a young person doesn’t mean I won’t put up a bad review or complaint.

A heartfelt thank you to Dr. David and Dr. Brian 

As a medical professional myself, I can genuinely say that meeting Dr. David, my father’s oncologist at Singapore National Cancer Centre (NCCS), has been one of the most inspiring experiences in this journey.

From the very first appointment, I could see his depth of knowledge, professionalism, and compassion. His clinical judgment is exceptional — calm, clear, and deeply reassuring. I’ve learned so much just by being in the room with him during my father’s visits.

Despite being told in Dubai that my father might have a new cancer, Dr. David’s expertise helped reveal that this was not the case. His careful review and insight proved that the earlier findings were incorrect — and for that, my entire family is deeply grateful. I’m truly happy I traveled all the way from Dubai for this opinion and treatment. It was absolutely worth it.

I also want to thank Dr. Brian, my father’s surgeon at Singapore General Hospital, for his excellent care and support throughout this process.

Thank you, Dr. David and Dr. Brian — you have both made a profound difference in our lives. Looking forward to seeing you again in three months, insha’Allah.

With heartfelt appreciation,

My father’s health was rapidly declining due to recurring dizziness and nausea episodes, and his recovery journey was initially very challenging. However, we are very grateful for the care he received at Outram Community Hospital, particularly from the team at Ward 9A.
I did not expect that my father could be discharged soon, but under the team led by Dr. Choo and along with the physio team supported by the incredibly warm assistant Mei Ling, he made significant progress on his physical condition. We were also fortunate to have the support of Dr. Tan Chieh Suey from SGH, who provided his expertise and advice for his recovery.
Our stay was made significantly more pleasant thanks to Nurse Leong Kai Man, whose experience and insight were invaluable. We are also grateful to the other dedicated nurses, including Zhou Yuhang; Ms. Lai, the dietitian, has also given us her thoughtful nutritional advice.
We would also like to extend our appreciation to the healthcare assistants, many of whom we didn’t have the chance to get their names, for their consistent support and kindness throughout our stay.

I am truly grateful for the excellent care provided by the National Cancer Centre Singapore (NCCS). From the very start, the process has been structured and well-organized. Everything, from making appointments to registration, medication prescriptions, and treatment, is handled efficiently.

The orientation for newcomers is very helpful, and I appreciate the thoughtful details like offering home delivery for medication at no extra charge. NCCS also provides comprehensive cancer support services, including call and clinic support for managing side effects and mental health advice, which has been incredibly valuable throughout the treatment journey.

The nursing team here provides exceptional support that, in many instances, can be better than what one might experience with private specialists. Their dedication and professionalism truly stand out. Though not all hospitals are perfect, NCCS does their best in ensuring patients feel supported and cared for. They also encourage continuous improvement by asking for online feedback after every visit.

Even though mask requirements have been lifted, I still wear one to protect myself, especially when there's news about flu bugs. The accessibility of the center is also a plus—it's a short walk to the SGH cafeteria, which is handy when the café on Level 2 is crowded or when I prefer other food options.

I want to extend my heartfelt thanks to the oncologists, pharmacists, and nurses who have cared for me throughout this year. Your dedication and expertise make all the difference.

My heartfelt appreciation to NCCS Staff Rose which extend her kindness and hospitality to us including my elderly father who does not speak English for his medical appt. Review Text:
Have been a patient of Dr Zhao Yan (赵医师) since the first time I saw her back in 2016. I came back to see her 2.5 years ago and have been regularly taking TCM meds, while undergoing monthly acupuncture treatment in the past few months. Acupuncture has been quite effective for me so far in relieving of my cramps and reducing blood clots, but I believe consistency is key to maintaining its effectiveness.

Am grateful most of all to have found an empathetic, personable, kind, caring, patient and helpful doctor who has always made me feel comfortable and at ease when sharing somewhat private details of my health issues, to best receive the most appropriate line of medical treatment. Dr Zhao is also professional and appears humble despite her seniority in the TCM field over years of experience. This makes me look forward to each consultation and treatment session with her, knowing I’m in good hands.

Personally, I would recommend NTU TCM clinic for those seeking TCM treatment in a clean, bright and aesthetically pleasing environment! Prices are quite reasonable compared to other clinics I’ve been to too.

Review Text:
Absolutely disappointed with the medical care at Central 24-HR Clinic (Pioneer North). My sister had a deep cut wound, and the nurse was kind enough to let her see the doctor quickly. But Dr. Andrew barely looked at her injury, didn’t examine it properly, and impatiently wrapped it with brown dressing—so tightly that her finger turned purple.

He dismissed it as minor, saying it would heal in a week. Thankfully, my parents didn’t feel right and took her to A&E. There, the hospital doctor said the wound was deep enough to see the bone, required an X-ray and five stitches, and even commented that the dressing used at the clinic is no longer recommended.

This clinic visit could have led to serious complications if we hadn’t sought a second opinion. Very poor judgment, no empathy, and unacceptable care.

Review Text:
Im leaving this feedback to express my dissatisfaction with the service I received at the clinic.

I visited the clinic with my husband and we registered at 6.15 PM. The lady counter staff informed us that the doctor would start seeing patients at 6.30 PM. My husband was running a fever and feeling very unwell, so we politely asked if we could sit on the waiting chairs while waiting just 15 more minutes? However, the lady counter staff firmly replied, "No."
I was shocked by the lack of empathy and professionalism. Is this really how you treat patients who are clearly unwell and in need of care? It’s not just about policy,  its about basic humanity pls.

Moreover, the waiting time was excessively long. Even after the doctor started at 6.30 PM, we were still waiting as patient number 5 at 7.30 PM, while patient number 4 was still inside with the doctor.

I sincerely hope the clinic takes this feedback seriously and makes an effort to improve both the attitude of the front-desk staff and the efficiency of your services. Patients come to a clinic for help — not to be treated coldly and made to wait in discomfort. There are already many negative reviews about this clinic, and I now understand why. I believe others had similar real experiences like ours. It’s not just people being harsh — it’s because they were genuinely disappointed and upset.

Rise & Grind Coffee Co.: A Promising Spot for Business Lunch with Room for Refinement

I chose Rise & Grind Coffee Co. for a recent business lunch, drawn by its reputation as a comfortable cafe. The setting was certainly pleasant, offering a relaxed and suitable environment for a midday meeting.

For my meal, I ordered the Pork Chop with Black Pepper Sauce. I must commend the kitchen on the marinade, which was clearly well-executed and delivered good flavour. However, I found the pork chop itself to be overcooked, resulting in a texture that was a little too tough. The long black I had was decent, serving its purpose as a coffee but not particularly standing out in its flavour profile.

In terms of service, it was okay. I noticed that a few tables required prompting before the crew came over to clean them, which felt a bit less proactive than I would have liked. On a prior note, the booking experience was not as smooth as it could have been, with the payment gateway presenting a bit of a challenge.

While the food and service were acceptable, there are certainly areas for improvement. A more attentive approach to table maintenance and a smoother booking process would enhance the overall experience. The pork chop has great potential, and with a little more care in the cooking, it could be a truly excellent dish.

Overall, Rise & Grind Coffee Co. is a fine choice for a casual business lunch due to its atmosphere. However, I hope they can refine their operational processes and consistency in the kitchen to better match their comfortable setting.

I think this is one of the more well-known cafés in the area. The atmosphere is great — very family-friendly, especially with the playground for kids. I’d say it’s a solid four-star café overall, but I’m giving five stars today to support them, as my dinner experience was peaceful and comfortable.

Their salmon pasta always sets me on fire — it’s the main reason I keep coming back! The sauce is creamy, and the salmon is perfectly cooked. I also tried the lamb burger, but it wasn’t really my type… especially the bun. Not sure how to describe it — maybe not fluffy enough? Honestly, even McD’s Angus burger buns might be better (JK!).

Thankfully, I also ordered the truffle cheese fries — not the best I’ve had, but still very tasty, nicely seasoned, and had a good truffle aroma.

We didn’t manage to try the desserts because we were too full from the mains — which shows the portion sizes are quite generous, and pricing feels reasonable.

I noticed other customers sharing one salmon pasta and pairing it with fries or dessert — honestly, that’s a smart way to enjoy more variety without over-ordering.

Visited this restaurant recently and was quite disappointed. The staff were not very polite, which affected the overall experience. The food was just average — nothing special in terms of taste. For the price charged, I expected a lot more, especially since the environment didn’t reflect the high cost either. Definitely not worth the value.
The experience was disappointing and upsetting. The quality of the food has declined, food does not justify by its quality, taste and environment. Everything is just disappointing.

The recent dining experience was upsetting. The quality of the food has noticeably declined; the salmon pasta was excessively buttery and oily, leading to discomfort. The spring pancake and fried chicken were also overly oily, and the meat was tough, strawberry matcha was underwhelming. The overall dining environment was also unfavorable, characterized by a hot and stuffy atmosphere and an unstable table, despite a reservation for corner seating. We would definitely not come back anymore and not recommend to our family and friends.

I visited Apricus Coffee during a non-peak period, thinking I could enjoy a cup of coffee while waiting for my friends to arrive. Upon entering, none of the staff greeted me, which was a bit odd given it wasn’t busy. I decided to take a seat at the bar stools near the entrance and cashier. The staff looked occupied, so I didn’t mind the lack of attention at first.

About 5 minutes later, a staff member approached me and asked if I was waiting for a table. I explained that I was waiting for friends and thought I’d have a coffee in the meantime. She then asked if I had a reservation, which caught me off guard—I wasn’t aware one was needed. I replied honestly, saying I didn’t know. She then asked what time my friends would arrive, and when I said around 6:30–7:00pm, she told me there would be a crowd coming at 7pm.

At that point, I felt uncomfortable and slightly offended—was I being indirectly told to leave? I reassured her that I just wanted to have my coffee and would leave before the crowd came. I ended up ordering my coffee and leaving shortly after.

While I understand if there were upcoming reservations, the way it was communicated made the experience feel unwelcoming. A bit more warmth and clarity would’ve gone a long way.

Review Text:
Updated review after clinic’s detailed explanation:
This clinic doesn’t offer subsidised vaccination pricing as per MOH subsidised rate guidelines despite booking via MOH site, so it’s definitely pricier than normal. Based on clinic’s explanation, only selected clinics may offer subsidised vaccination, and some may charge consultation fees. Maximum price for flu vaccine per MOH guidelines is $70 (based on clinic’s explanation) and that was what was charged & paid. Do check before heading over as we’ve had to pay almost 2x the price compared to other clinic. Other clinic only charged my family member $38 btw.

MAJOR REGRET not checking.

Update after seeing Dr Tang’s reply:
We did show Green CHAS card to the staff, but was still told there’s no subsidy at all (only CHAS chronic card is entitled for discount) even though MOH and Vaccine.gov.sg states that with Green CHAS card will be $35. We also booked the flu vaccine appointment via MOH’s website click through, assuming it’ll direct us to clinics under the same pricing scheme but had a rude shock when a nearby clinic from home charged my other family member $38.15 while this clinic charged us $70. Not sure where the discrepancies are or if this clinic just doesn’t offer subsidised rates per MOH’s guidelines. Jurong West ActiveSG Sports Complex is a gem in the heart of Singapore's western region. Perfectly equipped to cater to a wide range of fitness and recreational needs, it offers a welcoming environment for people of all ages and fitness levels.

One of the highlights of this sports complex is its state-of-the-art swimming pool. With clean and well-maintained facilities, including a kids’ pool, lap pool, and a wading pool, it’s a haven for swimmers and families looking for a refreshing day out. The lifeguards are attentive, ensuring safety for all.

Fitness enthusiasts will appreciate the well-equipped gym, featuring modern machines and spacious workout areas. The atmosphere is conducive to achieving fitness goals, with friendly staff always ready to assist. Additionally, the complex offers a variety of group classes such as yoga, Zumba, and aqua aerobics, catering to a wide range of interests.

The sports halls are another standout feature, accommodating sports like badminton, basketball, and table tennis. These facilities are well-maintained and ideal for friendly games or competitive events. The running tracks and outdoor spaces further enhance the appeal of the complex.

Accessibility is another advantage, with ample parking and proximity to public transport. The affordable entry fees and ActiveSG credits make it a cost-effective option for families and individuals alike.

Overall, Jurong West ActiveSG Sports Complex combines excellent facilities with a vibrant community atmosphere, making it a top choice for sports and recreation in Singapore. A visit here is always a rewarding experience!

Review Text:
July 2023: Updated July 2025
- Spacious, well ventilated (high ceiling and giant fans), mid-sized hawker center.
- Has a small wet market section with about a dozen stalls.
- Run by the Kopitiam Group.
- Can pay using PayNow/PayLah! QR, cash (getting uncommon), CDC vouchers or the NTUC app. Best using the NTUC app as you get a 10% discount.
- Stalls are not as many as the larger hawker centers, but I think there is enough variety for everyone.
- The biggest plus point is it's clean. The cleaning staff work rather efficiently to clean the floors and the tables. The dirty plates are also moved to the closed washing bay quickly.
- As a result, rarely see birds or pigeons and the hawker center is not littered with bird droppings.
- Most people return their plates and trays, but as always there are some who do not do their part (including. dirty wash basins, and toilets)...
- Kudos to the cleaning crew!
Address: 21 Sengkang W Ave, Fernvale Community Club

Review Text:
BFT Pioneer is one of the most friendiest and approachable coaches around! They are well-equipped with knowledge to teach members and motivate you during sessions :) Not only that, coaches are also certified and trained - so you know you are in good hands. 

Shower facilities are available to wash up right after a sweaty workout  And affordable isotonic and protein drinks to go.

Additionally, the coaches diligently communicate class schedules, workout and tips via their Instagram page @bft_pioneer and Telegram Channels for members. They show their commitment to members by building rapport with members in-and-out of studio, and value our satisfaction at the studio.

BFT Pioneer, similar to the other fellow member's reviews here, is my first group-style class I've sign up for. Generally members are welcoming & passionate to share their fitness knowledge and workout together. So don't be afraid if you are new and have no prior experience gyming! Come enjoy and have fun working out together 

Highly recommend to anyone interested to sign up for their trials or promotional try outs for the month!
Address: 511 Upper Jurong Rd, Block E-02-02A D'Arena

Review Text:
BFT Pioneer is by far best BFT I have been to. Boasting of an astonishing 200+ sq ft, it is safe to say that this is one the most spacious BFT around. The coaches are also very friendly and professional; always looking out for all of our heart rates to ensure we are pushing ourselves and improving progressively. They also diligently sanitise all the equipment between each sessions upkeep the hygiene and cleanliness for all the users. Location wise is fantastic; with various different eateries in the vicinity and ample parking spaces. They also do lend out their heart rate monitors for free for trial users! Major plus points all in all , you will definitely not regret joining BFT Pioneer!

Ps. Feel free to quote my name if you join if this review helped you

Review Text: Got that hk vibes and the staff are friendly. There is english picture menu available, and the food here is pretty good. I recommend the DIY noodles with soup and curry selections. And the daily soup is pretty great too. The only downside is perhaps the roasted duck rice has abit more meat as usually I would have the pieces with more bone than meat, and I would not be eating as much meat as I would expect for that price.
